SoPQuestionData = [{"newEra": {"sol": 50.0, "type": "newEra", "rep": 10.0, "text": "Two weeks ago, you said goodbye to your family in Russia. Now, after a land and sea voyage, you disembark in the port city of Haifa. The dry, hilly landscape looks alien to your eyes. \n\nYou arrive with a loaf of bread, a small amount of money and a dog-eared copy of Old New Land, Theodor Herzl's utopian vision of a new state for the Jewish people.\n\nThe Turkish customs agent asks for your visa. Then you wander the streets and souks of Haifa. Arab shopkeepers sell their wares. Mt. Carmel rises above the Mediterranean coast and the bustle of the port. In cafes and hostels, you debate with other Jewish immigrants how best to settle this land. \n\nThe next day, you visit the Palestine Office.", "pop": 10.0, "hook": "\"Welcome to Palestine!\"", "econ": 10.0}, "questions": [{"text": "\"Boker tov! We need young pioneers like you to build a new country,\" says the administator. \"I have a few questions before I assign you to a settlement group. First, what youth movement do you belong to?\" ", "answers": [{"answerBonusVariable": "", "answerIdeology": "", "rep": 5.0, "reply": "\"Good, good,\" he replies. \"You, too, believe in the international revolution of the working class!\" ", "sol": 5.0, "pop": 0.0, "answerBonusValue": 0.0, "econ": -5.0, "trig": "ideology", "answer": "Marxist"}, {"answerBonusVariable": "", "answerIdeology": "", "rep": 0.0, "reply": "\"Indeed,\" he replies. \"We must live from each according to his ability to each according to his needs.\" ", "sol": 0.0, "pop": 0.0, "answerBonusValue": 0.0, "econ": 0.0, "trig": "ideology", "answer": "Socialist"}, {"answerBonusVariable": "", "answerIdeology": "", "rep": 0.0, "reply": "\"Yes, let us build a new homeland for the Jews,\" he says. \"As Herzl wrote, 'If you will it, it's not a dream.'\"", "sol": -5.0, "pop": 0.0, "answerBonusValue": 0.0, "econ": 10.0, "trig": "ideology", "answer": "Labor Zionist"}, {"answerBonusVariable": "", "answerIdeology": "", "rep": 0.0, "reply": "\"Amen,\" he says. \"Our people's return to the Promised Land is divine will.\" ", "sol": 5.0, "pop": 5.0, "answerBonusValue": 0.0, "econ": -5.0, "trig": "ideology", "answer": "Religious"}], "type": "setup", "hook": "\"Welcome to Palestine!\""}, {"text": "The administrator scratches your answers on a file. \"Taming this land isn't for the weak of heart or body,\" he warns as he unfolds a map. \"Where in Palestine do you want to begin?\" ", "answers": [{"answerBonusVariable": "", "answerIdeology": "", "rep": 10.0, "reply": "\"Ah, a true adventurer!\" he says. \"We will send you to the mountains past Lake Kinnereth.\"", "sol": 0.0, "pop": 0.0, "answerBonusValue": 0.0, "econ": 0.0, "trig": "location", "answer": "The North"}, {"answerBonusVariable": "", "answerIdeology": "", "rep": 0.0, "reply": "\"Truly, the way of the pioneers,\" he replies. \"You will settle the legendary Jezreel Valley of the Galilee.\"", "sol": 5.0, "pop": 5.0, "answerBonusValue": 0.0, "econ": 0.0, "trig": "location", "answer": "The East"}, {"answerBonusVariable": "", "answerIdeology": "", "rep": -5.0, "reply": "\"A safe choice,\" he tells you. \"You can build along the coastal plain of the Mediterranean.\"", "sol": 0.0, "pop": 5.0, "answerBonusValue": 0.0, "econ": 10.0, "trig": "location", "answer": "The South\n"}], "type": "setup", "hook": "\"Welcome to Palestine!\""}]}, {"newEra": {"sol": 0.0, "type": "newEra", "rep": 0.0, "text": "You meet your new comrades at a training farm outside of Haifa. Together, you will work as a collective and vote on all decisions in a General Assembly. \n\nYou travel for days and arrive at a plot of land purchased by the Jewish National Fund. You set up tents and break ground. When night falls, you join hands and dance the hora under the flickering stars.\n\nAs settlers of Palestine, you will build a village and live as absolute equals. You will found a nation. You will heal the world.\n\nA few months later, your kibbutz faces its first dilemma...", "pop": 0.0, "hook": "1910-1918: Founding of the Kibbutz", "econ": 0.0}, "questions": [{"text": "\nMiriam wants to study livestock-raising techniques with an Arab farmer in the next village.\n\n\"It's too dangerous!\" warns Moishe.  \"And raising cows is a man's job.\"\n\nWhat do you recommend to the Assembly?", "answers": [{"answerBonusVariable": "rep", "answerIdeology": "Marxist", "rep": 5.0, "reply": "A few members resent Miriam working with the Arab farmer But she becomes adept at raising cattle and the dairy operation adds to your profits. More female members join your community.", "sol": -5.0, "pop": 5.0, "answerBonusValue": 5.0, "econ": 5.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Let Miriam apprentice with the Arab farmer."}, {"answerBonusVariable": "rep", "answerIdeology": "Socialist", "rep": 0.0, "reply": "Miriam learns techniques to expand the cattle operation. Later, she travels to Holland for more training.  ", "sol": 0.0, "pop": 0.0, "answerBonusValue": 10.0, "econ": 10.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Send her to a Jewish training farm."}, {"answerBonusVariable": "rep", "answerIdeology": "Religious", "rep": 0.0, "reply": "Miriam and her husband leave the kibbutz to find a truly equal community. It takes another year to start raising cows.", "sol": 5.0, "pop": -2.0, "answerBonusValue": 5.0, "econ": 0.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Ask her to look after the vegetable garden instead."}], "type": "I", "hook": "\"I want to learn how to raise cattle!\""}, {"text": "A married couple celebrates the birth of the first child on your kibbutz and plans to name him. \n\n\"As a commune, we must vote on everything,\" argues Shmuel, \"including the names of new members.\"\n\nWho should name the child?", "answers": [{"answerBonusVariable": "sol", "answerIdeology": "Socialist", "rep": 0.0, "reply": "The parents name their boy Gideon. He grows up to be a leader in your kibbutz.", "sol": 5.0, "pop": 5.0, "answerBonusValue": -10.0, "econ": 5.0, "trig": "", "answer": "The parents alone."}, {"answerBonusVariable": "rep", "answerIdeology": "Socialist", "rep": 10.0, "reply": "The Assembly votes to name the boy Benzion. The family eventually leaves the kibbutz for a town where life is less restrictive. ", "sol": -5.0, "pop": -5.0, "answerBonusValue": 10.0, "econ": 0.0, "trig": "", "answer": "The kibbutz, by vote."}], "type": "I", "hook": "\"Who should name the child?\""}, {"text": "On your plot of land, you find trees planted by hired Arab labour.\n\n\"The land will not be ours unless we develop it with Jewish labour!\" declares Moishe. \n\n\"Who cares?\" replies Yosef. \"Let's focus on the future not the past.\"\n\nWhat do you do about the trees? ", "answers": [{"answerBonusVariable": "sol", "answerIdeology": "Marxist", "rep": 5.0, "reply": "You cut down the trees and plant new ones. The legend of your uncompromising pioneer spirit spreads throughout the land.", "sol": 0.0, "pop": 0.0, "answerBonusValue": -5.0, "econ": 0.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Remove the trees and plant new ones."}, {"answerBonusVariable": "rep", "answerIdeology": "Labor Zionist", "rep": 0.0, "reply": "The trees stay. You plant more. The orchards provide fruit and income in your early years.", "sol": 0.0, "pop": 0.0, "answerBonusValue": -5.0, "econ": 5.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Leave the trees."}], "type": "E", "hook": "\"We must plant with our own hands!\""}, {"text": "You discover that the land bought for your kibbutz by the Jewish National Fund displaced Arab families.\n\n \"Our land was bought legally,\" argues Shmuel. \n\n\"What about being good neighbours?\" says Miriam.\n\nWhat do you do about these past tenants?", "answers": [{"answerBonusVariable": "rep", "answerIdeology": "Marxist", "rep": 5.0, "reply": "The decision to return the land sparks an angry debate. Your kibbutz struggles without the meagre earnings of the farmland. But your act of solidarity inspires fellow socialists.", "sol": -5.0, "pop": 0.0, "answerBonusValue": 10.0, "econ": 0.75, "trig": "", "answer": "You give the property to the Arab farmers. "}, {"answerBonusVariable": "rep", "answerIdeology": "Labor Zionist", "rep": 0.0, "reply": "The Zionist Agency holds a deed to the land. It's your job now to make it bloom. And so your members unite to do that.", "sol": 0.0, "pop": 5.0, "answerBonusValue": 10.0, "econ": 10.0, "trig": "", "answer": "You cultivate the fields that are now legally yours."}, {"answerBonusVariable": "sol", "answerIdeology": "Socialist", "rep": -5.0, "reply": "Members are uncertain about this compromise. But in the years to come, they learn to trust their Arab neighbours. New members are drawn to your thriving kibbutz.", "sol": 0.0, "pop": 10.0, "answerBonusValue": -5.0, "econ": 1.25, "trig": "", "answer": "You keep the fields but rent some back to the tenant farmers."}], "type": "E", "hook": "\"This is a land without a people for a people without a land!\""}, {"text": "War breaks out in Europe and spreads to Palestine. Turkish authorities block Jewish immigration, restrict imports and exports, and look upon your settlements with suspicion. Some Jewish immigrants leave Palestine for America. \n\n\"We must stay united to survive,\" says Sarah.\n\nHow do you respond? ", "answers": [{"answerBonusVariable": "rep ", "answerIdeology": "Socialist", "rep": 5.0, "reply": "Secret meetings forge alliances between different kibbutzes. This will become a federation that will help lead your members and the state of Israel.", "sol": 0.0, "pop": 0.0, "answerBonusValue": 5.0, "econ": 10.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Coordinate production efforts with other kibbutzes.\n"}, {"answerBonusVariable": "rep", "answerIdeology": "Labor Zionist", "rep": 5.0, "reply": "Several members volunteer for the militia. Some are killed during the war. Their bravery inspires your community and heightens its legend as a defender of the frontier.", "sol": 5.0, "pop": -5.0, "answerBonusValue": 10.0, "econ": 0.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Set up a militia to defend your settlements against the Turks.\n"}, {"answerBonusVariable": "rep", "answerIdeology": "Religious", "rep": 5.0, "reply": "You help new arrivals infiltrate Palestine and integrate them into your settlement. They will expand your community once the armistice is signed.", "sol": 0.0, "pop": 10.0, "answerBonusValue": 5.0, "econ": 5.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Help to smuggle immigrants into Palestine."}], "type": "E", "hook": "\"Our people need our help!\""}, {"text": "A volunteer from Europe takes a cigarette break at the end of every furrow he ploughs.  \"He's a poor pioneer!\" complains Moishe. \"Send him home!\"\n\n\"He's fine,\" says Yosef. \"From each according to his ability. And that's his ability.\"\n\nWhat do you do about the lazy volunteer?\n", "answers": [{"answerBonusVariable": "sol", "answerIdeology": "Socialist", "rep": 5.0, "reply": "Your decision to exile this \"free rider\" establishes a high work ethic among your founders. Other kibbutzes take note.", "sol": 5.0, "pop": -2.0, "answerBonusValue": -10.0, "econ": -5.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Ask him to leave."}, {"answerBonusVariable": "rep", "answerIdeology": "Religious", "rep": 0.0, "reply": "The new worker stays. Members still complain about doing more work to make up for his slow pace.", "sol": -5.0, "pop": 2.0, "answerBonusValue": 5.0, "econ": 5.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Let him stay.\n"}], "type": "I", "hook": "\"He's lazy! He has to leave!\""}, {"text": "Arab brigands ambush and wound a kibbutznik outside the kibbutz. \n\n\"We must retaliate!\" says Itzik. \"This cannot go unpunished.\"\n\n\"Let's not provoke more attacks,\" cautions Sarah. \n\nHow should you protect the kibbutz? ", "answers": [{"answerBonusVariable": "sol", "answerIdeology": "Marxist", "rep": 5.0, "reply": "The posse of kibbutzniks scour the area for weeks and ignore their work. Finally, they confront a band of suspects. One kibbutz member is killed. But the attacks stop. Jewish immigrants read about your members' bravery on the frontier.", "sol": 5.0, "pop": -2.0, "answerBonusValue": -5.0, "econ": -5.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Send a posse to track down the attackers.\n"}, {"answerBonusVariable": "rep", "answerIdeology": "Religious", "rep": 0.0, "reply": "Your kibbutz members agree to ignore the threat and focus on cultivating crops. A good harvest is the best revenge, although not everyone agrees.", "sol": -5.0, "pop": 0.0, "answerBonusValue": 5.0, "econ": 5.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Ignore the incident."}, {"answerBonusVariable": "rep", "answerIdeology": "Labor Zionist", "rep": 5.0, "reply": "You never discover the culprits behind the ambush. But you train a defensive militia and develop a reputation as fighters as well as farmers.", "sol": 0.0, "pop": 5.0, "answerBonusValue": 5.0, "econ": 0.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Organize a militia with nearby kibbutzes.\n"}], "type": "E", "hook": "\"They will only understand force!\""}, {"text": "An eccentric middle-aged immigrant from Russian arrives on your kibbutz. He has no interest in becoming a member but volunteers to labour in your fields and speaks in philosophical aphorisms. \n\n\"The Jewish people have sinned through not working!\" he preaches \"Collective life will create a new people on this land!\" \n\n\"The old man is a distraction from real work,\" complains Shmuel.\n\n\"No, no!\" says Sarah. \"His philosophy will lead us to greatness!\"\n\nWhat do you do about the bearded philosopher?", "answers": [{"answerBonusVariable": "sol", "answerIdeology": "Labor Zionist", "rep": -5.0, "reply": "The bearded philosopher leaves. \"I am loyal to no insttution,\" he says. \"Only to redeeming the land of Israel.\" Several members follow the guru on his wanderings. Everyone else gets get back to work.", "sol": 0.0, "pop": -5.0, "answerBonusValue": -5.0, "econ": 5.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Ask him to leave.\n"}, {"answerBonusVariable": "rep", "answerIdeology": "Religious", "rep": 0.0, "reply": "The bearded philosopher fades into the background of kibbutz life, toiling in the fields and sharing his ideas with a few kibbutzniks in the evening. His inspiring words relieve the tedium of the long work days. ", "sol": 5.0, "pop": 0.0, "answerBonusValue": 5.0, "econ": 0.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Let him stay as a volunteer."}, {"answerBonusVariable": "rep", "answerIdeology": "Labor Zionist", "rep": 5.0, "reply": "You turn over many meetings of the General Assembly to speeches by this  thinker. The field work doesn't always get done, but your kibbutz gains sense of higher purpose. ", "sol": 5.0, "pop": 0.0, "answerBonusValue": 5.0, "econ": -5.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Devote extra time to studying his philosophy.\n"}], "type": "I", "hook": "\"We must listen for he speaks great truths!\""}, {"text": "Golda, a young immigrant from America, wears pressed clothes and tells the General Assembly to buy new drinking glasses for the dining room. \n\n\"Enough of her airs,\" complains Moishe. \"She isn't ready to be a pioneer.\" \n\nWhat do you do about Golda?\n", "answers": [{"answerBonusVariable": "rep", "answerIdeology": "Religious", "rep": -5.0, "reply": "Kicking out the fancy American pleases some of your members. Years later, your kibbutz becomes notorious for rejecting Golda Meir, the fourth Prime Minister of Israel.", "sol": 5.0, "pop": -2.0, "answerBonusValue": 5.0, "econ": 0.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Ask her to leave."}, {"answerBonusVariable": "sol", "answerIdeology": "Marxist", "rep": 0.0, "reply": "The American tones down her demands and sacrifices her own desires to fit into the kibbutz. Your community feels bland, but you have suppressed envy and pride. For now.", "sol": 5.0, "pop": 0.0, "answerBonusValue": 5.0, "econ": 5.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Tell her that a good kibbutznik is never materialistic and she should share her dresses.\n"}, {"answerBonusVariable": "rep", "answerIdeology": "Labor Zionist", "rep": 5.0, "reply": "Some members resent the fancy American. Most come to accept her work ethic. Later, Golda Meir, Israel's fourth Prime Minister of Israel, will remember the generosity of your members.", "sol": -5.0, "pop": 5.0, "answerBonusValue": 10.0, "econ": -5.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Ignore the gossips and buy new glassware."}], "type": "I", "hook": "\"She thinks she's more fancy than the rest of us!\""}, {"text": "Rachel, a young member, returns after a year in Russia and volunteers to teach in the kibbutz school until a doctor diagnoses her with tuberculosis. \n\n\"She might infect the children,\" cautions Sarah, who runs the children's house.\n\nWhat do you suggest?\n", "answers": [{"answerBonusVariable": "rep", "answerIdeology": "Labor Zionist", "rep": -5.0, "reply": "It's a tough decision, but the safety of the children comes first. Rachel relocates to the city, where she writes poetry and slowly succumbs to TB. Her collected poems are published to great popularity. You become known as the kibbutz that exiled Rachel the Poetess from Eden.", "sol": 5.0, "pop": -5.0, "answerBonusValue": -5.0, "econ": 0.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Ask her to leave to get treated in the city.\n"}, {"answerBonusVariable": "sol", "answerIdeology": "Religious", "rep": 5.0, "reply": "Several younger members die of TB over the next few years. Rachel publishes poems about life on the kibbutz and immigrating to Palestine that one day become the anthem of a nation.", "sol": -5.0, "pop": -5.0, "answerBonusValue": 5.0, "econ": 0.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Let her stay and hope the infection doesn't spread.\n"}], "type": "I", "hook": "\"What about the children?\""}, {"text": "The land assigned to your kibbutz was chosen for its strategic value. But little grows in the dry, rocky soil. You can see lush and fertile fields in the distance. \n\n\"We should ask to relocate,\" says Yosef. \"Or members will leave.\"\n\nWhat do you decide?", "answers": [{"answerBonusVariable": "rep", "answerIdeology": "Socialist", "rep": 10.0, "reply": "Your members tough it out on the rocky, dangerous terrain. Several leave because of the extra work. The rest of you work together to build an outpost that will defend and define a new nation. ", "sol": 0.0, "pop": 0.0, "answerBonusValue": 5.0, "econ": -5.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Stay on the land you've been assigned to defend."}, {"answerBonusVariable": "rep", "answerIdeology": "Labor Zionist", "rep": -5.0, "reply": "You convince the Zionist Agency to give your plot of land to a new group of settlers. You move your kibbutz from the rocky outcrop to a fertile swath of valley. Your first crops are bountiful. But other kibbutzniks mock your \"quitter's spirit\" and wonder if you are true pioneers. ", "sol": 5.0, "pop": 1.25, "answerBonusValue": -10.0, "econ": 1.5, "trig": "", "answer": "Ask the Palestine Office for a better location."}], "type": "E", "hook": "\"We can't feed ourselves, let alone a nation!\""}, {"text": "Your fields and farming operations now provide more than just subsistence.  You harvest enough to sell in bulk. \n\n\"We should join the new co-operative,\" says Yosef. \"They will help with distribution and marketing.\" \n\nMoishe, the cowshed manager, thinks you can earn more money by cutting out any middle-men.\n\nHow do you sell your kibbutz's products?\n", "answers": [{"answerBonusVariable": "rep ", "answerIdeology": "Socialist", "rep": 5.0, "reply": "With your support, the milk co-op becomes a force within Palestine and lays the economic foundation for the Jewish State. ", "sol": 0.0, "pop": 0.0, "answerBonusValue": 5.0, "econ": 10.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Join the co-operative."}, {"answerBonusVariable": "econ", "answerIdeology": "Labor Zionist", "rep": 0.0, "reply": "Your members sell the milk on their own but not for as much as you estimated. Still, the effort makes your feel like true pioneers. You feel you can tackle any challenge.", "sol": 5.0, "pop": 0.0, "answerBonusValue": 10.0, "econ": 5.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Market and sell on your own."}], "type": "E", "hook": "\"We can make more profit on our own.\""}]}, {"newEra": {"sol": 0.0, "type": "newEra", "rep": 0.0, "text": "\nWhat began as a small commune (or \"kvutsa\") has become a larger community (or \"kibbutz\"). In the Great War, Britain drives the Ottomans out of Palestine. The Balfour Declaration promises a homeland for the Jews. Every day brings you closer to fulfilling Herzl's dream. \n\nAnd yet frontier life remains a struggle: drought, malaria, long days in the field. Confidence wavers in your comrades. How can you create utopia? Who will feed the waves of new immigrants? \n\nAnd now you hear reports that your Arab neighbours do not welcome new Jewish settlements. There are new worries every day...", "pop": 1.5, "hook": "1919-1936: British Mandate", "econ": 1.5}, "questions": [{"text": "Arab protesters attack nearby kibbutzes and villages. One day, a one-armed veteran of the Russo-Japanese War arrives with a small Jewish militia. \n\n\"I need volunteers to build fortifications and track down the attackers,\" he says. Several younger members want to volunteer. \n\nWhat do you tell the veteran? \n", "answers": [{"answerBonusVariable": "rep", "answerIdeology": "Labor Zionist", "rep": 10.0, "reply": "Five of your strongest young men join Joseph Trumpeldor, the veteran. Trumpeldor and four of your comrades die defending Tel Hai from Arab attackers. Your kibbutz is often memorialized in the homages to this famous martyr.", "sol": 0.0, "pop": -5.0, "answerBonusValue": 5.0, "econ": -5.0, "trig": "", "answer": "He can take your bravest kibbutzniks for his militia.\n"}, {"answerBonusVariable": "sol", "answerIdeology": "Religious", "rep": 5.0, "reply": "Younger members grumble about not letting them fight with the veteran. But you are relieved they stay to help with the harvest rather than die alongside Josef Trumpeldor in the defense of Tel Hai. ", "sol": -5.0, "pop": 0.0, "answerBonusValue": 10.0, "econ": 5.0, "trig": "", "answer": "You don't want to provoke the Arabs. Your kibbutz can defend itself."}, {"answerBonusVariable": "sol", "answerIdeology": "Labor Zionist", "rep": 0.0, "reply": "Many members are unhappy that the kibbutz relies on the British to defend a Jewish settlement. But the extra attention of the Mandate authorities allows your kibbutzniks to cultivate your fields without worry.", "sol": -5.0, "pop": 0.0, "answerBonusValue": -5.0, "econ": 10.0, "trig": "", "answer": "You are all under British rule now. Let the Mandate authorities deal with the Arabs."}], "type": "E", "hook": "\"Who will join my cause?\""}, {"text": "Two members committed suicide in the past year, a boy and a girl, each only 18 years old. The long hours of work, the separation from families, the tough conditions in a foreign land proved too much. The strain is showing on other comrades.\n\n\"We must escape this godforsaken place,\" Yosef argues, \"and find a more promising settlement in the Promised Land!\" \n\nWhat do you recommend?", "answers": [{"answerBonusVariable": "sol", "answerIdeology": "Marxist", "rep": -5.0, "reply": "Your new location is near a town and relieves the solitude of your members. The kibbutz thrives. But you must wear the mantle of \"the kibbutz that quit.\" ", "sol": 0.0, "pop": 1.25, "answerBonusValue": -5.0, "econ": 1.5, "trig": "", "answer": "Move the kibbutz to a less-remote location."}, {"answerBonusVariable": "rep", "answerIdeology": "Labor Zionist", "rep": 1.5, "reply": "Conditions on your remote location improve slowly. Several members sneak away in the middle of the night, which is better than taking their own lives. The Jewish Agency celebrates you as true pioneers.", "sol": -5.0, "pop": -5.0, "answerBonusValue": 5.0, "econ": 0.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Settle the frontier, no matter the cost."}], "type": "E", "hook": "\"How many more must die? We have suffered enough!\""}, {"text": "A young author travels from Germany to your kibbutz. He wants to write about the heroic struggle of the Jewish pioneers, what he calls \"the chronicle of an experiment\". He might be a good writer but he is a slow worker who complains about conditions. \n\n\"I'm sure his work ethic will improve,\" says Sarah, when he asks to become a member.\n\n\"Bah!\" says Shmuel. \"He can finish novel back in Berlin!\"\n\nWhat do you recommend? ", "answers": [{"answerBonusVariable": "rep", "answerIdeology": "Socialist", "rep": 5.0, "reply": "The novelist doesn't improve much as a labourer. Members resent his constant complaints and malingering. Eventually, he quits, leaves Palestine and writes a heroic novel about the founding of your kibbutz. ", "sol": -5.0, "pop": -2.0, "answerBonusValue": 5.0, "econ": 0.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Accept the novelist as a member.\n"}, {"answerBonusVariable": "rep", "answerIdeology": "Labor Zionist", "rep": -5.0, "reply": "Everyone is relieved when the novelist is rejected for membership. Years later, he takes his revenge by writing a novel about a commune of self-important pioneers who don't appreciate true art.", "sol": 5.0, "pop": -2.0, "answerBonusValue": -5.0, "econ": 5.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Recommend he be dismissed."}], "type": "I", "hook": "\"We need farmers not novelists!\""}, {"text": "Ardent Marxists on your kibbutz believe the international revolution is near. Zionism is a distraction. \n\n\"Let's start a commune in the Soviet Union,\" says Igor, the leader. \"We can build utopia for the working people!\" He wants other kibbutzniks to join the exodus. But many members think they are naive.\n\n What do you tell them? ", "answers": [{"answerBonusVariable": "rep", "answerIdeology": "Marxist", "rep": 5.0, "reply": "A large group of young members leave for the Soviet Union. You never hear from them again. Their labour is missed, but the remaining kibbutzniks are relieved not to be subjected to their political lectures at every Assembly.", "sol": 5.0, "pop": 0.75, "answerBonusValue": 5.0, "econ": -5.0, "trig": "", "answer": "They are welcome to build a new society in the USSR.\n"}, {"answerBonusVariable": "rep", "answerIdeology": "Socialist", "rep": 10.0, "reply": "Only a few young members leave for the Soviet Union. You never hear from them again after the Russian Revolution turns to tyranny.  ", "sol": 0.0, "pop": -5.0, "answerBonusValue": 5.0, "econ": 0.0, "trig": "", "answer": "They are dupes of Lenin and shouldn't come back when their foolish enterprise fails.\n"}], "type": "I", "hook": "\"Fools, there is nothing for you in the Soviet Union!\""}, {"text": "Your population has grown so that the General Assembly can no longer sit around a table in the dining room. Meetings go on for hours. \n\n\"Small is beautiful,\" says Moishe. \"We should split and start a new kibbutz.\" \n\nOthers disagree. \"Only by growing can we settle Palestine,\" says Sarah, \"and change the world.\" \n\nWhat do you recommend?", "answers": [{"answerBonusVariable": "rep", "answerIdeology": "Socialist", "rep": 10.0, "reply": "It's a difficult decision. Long-time friends agree to divide the community. And yet it works. You inspire other collectives to recognize the limitations of endless expansion.", "sol": 5.0, "pop": 0.5, "answerBonusValue": 10.0, "econ": 10.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Split the community into two kibbutzes."}, {"answerBonusVariable": "rep", "answerIdeology": "Labor Zionist", "rep": 0.0, "reply": "The kibbutz rapidly expands over the next few years. Not everyone gets along with the new arrivals. But the kibbutz becomes an economic force in the region and a leader in the movement.", "sol": 0.75, "pop": 2.5, "answerBonusValue": 10.0, "econ": 20.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Attract more members and expand rapidly.\n"}, {"answerBonusVariable": "pop", "answerIdeology": "Marxist", "rep": 0.75, "reply": "The safe choice satisfies few members. Smaller communities provide more intimacy. Larger ones have more economic and political muscle. Your members envy other kibbutzes with a clear vision.", "sol": -5.0, "pop": 5.0, "answerBonusValue": -5.0, "econ": 0.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Maintain your current size."}], "type": "B", "hook": "\"Can we live as one?\""}, {"text": "Your founding families are divided about the best way for the kibbutz to grow. \n\n\"If any Jewish immigrant wants to be a kibbutznik, we should accept them,\" argues Yosef. \"Everyone can be trained.\" \n\nOthers members disagree. \"Early education is vital,\" says Miriam. \"We must only take new members from our youth movemens, so they are ready to be kibbutzniks.\" \n\nWhat do you recommend? ", "answers": [{"answerBonusVariable": "rep ", "answerIdeology": "Marxist", "rep": 0.0, "reply": "You kibbutz flourishes with the influx of new members. Debates at the Assembly become less about socialism and more about the economy of your community. Not everyone gets along.", "sol": -5.0, "pop": 1.25, "answerBonusValue": -5.0, "econ": 1.5, "trig": "", "answer": "Take anyone who wants to join."}, {"answerBonusVariable": "rep", "answerIdeology": "Marxist", "rep": 5.0, "reply": "Your kibbutz grows slowly as you add members from the same youth movement. These newcomers bring a fresh passion for work,  Zionism and the kibbutz.", "sol": 5.0, "pop": 5.0, "answerBonusValue": 5.0, "econ": 1.25, "trig": "", "answer": "Only take members from your youth movement."}], "type": "I", "hook": "\"Communal life is not for everyone!\""}, {"text": "The Great Depression hits Palestine, too. Many Jewish immigrants return to Europe. Several members see no future on the kibbutz and threaten to leave if conditions don't improve.\n\n \"Let us take jobs in town or on a private farm!\" argues Yosef. \"We can't stick to farming.\"\n\nWhat do you advise?", "answers": [{"answerBonusVariable": "sol", "answerIdeology": "Marxist", "rep": 0.0, "reply": "Members who work outside the kibbutz bring new wealth to your community. Other kibbutzniks accuse them of not turning over all their wages. Still, the freedom to work outside the kibbutz draws new members.", "sol": -5.0, "pop": 5.0, "answerBonusValue": -5.0, "econ": 10.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Members can work in town if they give their money to the kibbutz.\n"}, {"answerBonusVariable": "rep", "answerIdeology": "Socialist", "rep": 10.0, "reply": "It's a difficult year as your kibbutz nearly runs out of funds. Several members leave for town. But the remaining community grows stronger. The capitalist system is failing, and together you will build a new society.", "sol": 0.0, "pop": 0.9, "answerBonusValue": 5.0, "econ": 0.75, "trig": "", "answer": "Everyone must follow the job rotation and only work for the kibbutz.\n"}], "type": "E", "hook": "\"Let us work in town or we'll starve!\""}, {"text": "You need to drain a swamp so that the kibbutz can add fields, but it's too much work for your members. \n\n\"Let's hire help now,\" suggests Moishe.\n\n\"No, we must do the work ourselves,\" cautions Miriam. \"Let's wait until we have enough hands.\"\n\nWhat do you suggest?", "answers": [{"answerBonusVariable": "rep", "answerIdeology": "Labor Zionist", "rep": -5.0, "reply": "With the swamp drained, crops take root in your new fields. Who cares if other kibbutzniks accuse you of breaking the philsophy of \"self labour.\" ", "sol": 0.0, "pop": 0.0, "answerBonusValue": -10.0, "econ": 10.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Hire outside labour from an Arab village.\n"}, {"answerBonusVariable": "sol", "answerIdeology": "Marxist", "rep": 0.0, "reply": "It takes longer, but the swamp gets drained and you forge new bonds with the neighbouring kibbutzim.", "sol": 5.0, "pop": 10.0, "answerBonusValue": -5.0, "econ": 5.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Ask for help from a nearby kibbutz in exchange for half the fields."}, {"answerBonusVariable": "pop", "answerIdeology": "Religious", "rep": 5.0, "reply": "It's hard to make a living surrounded by marsh and swamp. But your kibbutz makes do until you have more helping hands.", "sol": 0.0, "pop": 5.0, "answerBonusValue": 5.0, "econ": 0.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Wait till you have more members.\n"}], "type": "I", "hook": "\"Neither exploiter nor exploited, that's our motto!\""}, {"text": "You want to move beyond subsistence farming, but you must decide on which type of cash crop to plant. Some members suggest citrus.\n\n \"No,\" argues Moishe. \"A tobacco plantation is more lucrative.\" \n\n\"Forget farming,\" says Itzik. \"We should open a metalworks factory.\" \n\nWhere do you invest your resources?", "answers": [{"answerBonusVariable": "rep", "answerIdeology": "Socialist", "rep": 5.0, "reply": "Citrus proves to be a good choice. The trees flourish. New members arrive to help with harvest. And the international reputation for Palestine's Jaffa oranges raises the profile of your kibbutz.", "sol": 0.0, "pop": 5.0, "answerBonusValue": 5.0, "econ": 10.0, "trig": "", "answer": "An orange orchard."}, {"answerBonusVariable": "rep", "answerIdeology": "Religious", "rep": 0.0, "reply": "Your make a little money but then your profits flatline. Your fields are not well-suited to tobacco. The market is saturated with competitors' products", "sol": -5.0, "pop": 5.0, "answerBonusValue": -10.0, "econ": 0.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Tobacco fields."}, {"answerBonusVariable": "rep", "answerIdeology": "Labor Zionist", "rep": 0.0, "reply": "The factory is a success and attracts new members. Some founders lament that kibbutzniks are no longer reclaiming the land of Israel by working its soil.", "sol": -5.0, "pop": 5.0, "answerBonusValue": 10.0, "econ": 10.0, "trig": "", "answer": "A metalworks factory."}], "type": "E", "hook": "\"Oranges are like gold!\""}]}, {"newEra": {"sol": 0.0, "type": "newEra", "rep": 0.0, "text": "\nDarkness spreads over Europe. The Nazis rise to the power in a spectacle of brown shirts and broken glass. War is on the horizon. You urge family members there to leave before it's too late. For many, it will be. \n\nPalestine suffers under the global Depression. Tensions rise between Arab populations and Jewish colonists. The British Government releases the White Paper and reneges on its promise of a Jewish homeland.\n\nAnd your own small community struggles to survive.", "pop": 0.0, "hook": "1937-1945: The Coming of War", "econ": -5.0}, "questions": [{"text": "The nightwatchman hears a strange whistling and discovers that Haviva owns a personal tea kettle, in violation of your philosophy of no private property. \n\n\"What does it matter?\" she replies. \n\n\"If everyone has a kettle,\" says Hannah, \"nobody will go to the common room and we will live as isolated as city folk.\" \n\nWhat should you do about the \"problem of the tea kettle\"?", "answers": [{"answerBonusVariable": "rep", "answerIdeology": "Religious", "rep": 5.0, "reply": "After a few weeks of being ostracized by the kibbutz, Haviva and her husband pack up their kettle and leave. Nobody brings private property into the kibbutz again for years.", "sol": 5.0, "pop": -5.0, "answerBonusValue": 0.0, "econ": 0.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Haviva can keep her kettle."}, {"answerBonusVariable": "rep", "answerIdeology": "Labor Zionist", "rep": 10.0, "reply": "Haviva is embarrassed to have her kettle confiscated but agrees to let the kibbutz use it collectively. She joins the other members for tea, cards and gossip. ", "sol": 5.0, "pop": 0.0, "answerBonusValue": -15.0, "econ": 0.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Confiscate the kettle and add it to the common room."}, {"answerBonusVariable": "rep", "answerIdeology": "Marxist", "rep": 0.0, "reply": "Everyone is delighted to get their own kettle, despite the costs to the kibbutz. At nightfall, not as many people visit the common lounge after dinner.", "sol": -5.0, "pop": 5.0, "answerBonusValue": -5.0, "econ": -5.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Buy every member a personal kettle."}], "type": "I", "hook": "\"What's that strange whistling from Hannah's room?\""}, {"text": "Your membership has grown faster than your housing. You now have a problem with \"the third one,\"  an extra kibbutznik who must share an apartment with a married couple due to lack of space. \n\n\"My wife and I haven't been, uh, intimate in months!\" laments Yosef. \n\n\"Neither have I,\" says Dudu, the bachelor who shares their room.  Other members say it's a petty issue.\n\nWhat do you do about the \"third one\"?", "answers": [{"answerBonusVariable": "sol", "answerIdeology": "Religious", "rep": 5.0, "reply": "Keeping the cramped quarters saves money in the short term. But several members move to a kibbutz with more space. And others gossip that some couples are enjoying the \"third one\" more than others...  ", "sol": -5.0, "pop": -5.0, "answerBonusValue": -5.0, "econ": 0.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Only build new rooms when you have more money."}, {"answerBonusVariable": "sol", "answerIdeology": "Marxist", "rep": 0.0, "reply": "It's a big budget hit but the new housing units helps your kibbutz expand while maintaining peace between neighbours. New members are drawn to your community.", "sol": 5.0, "pop": 10.0, "answerBonusValue": -10.0, "econ": -10.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Borrow money to build new apartments."}], "type": "I", "hook": "\"What a bourgeois issue!\""}, {"text": "Kibbutz decision-making has become unwieldy. Assembly meetings go on for hours and are dominated by the loudest voices.\n\n\"Must we vote on everything?\" laments Yosef.\n\nAre there better ways to manage your community?", "answers": [{"answerBonusVariable": "sol", "answerIdeology": "Marxist", "rep": -5.0, "reply": "The bureaucratization of your kibbutz begins. Committees beget more committees. Nobody is entirely happy with the results, but  the administrative work gets done. And the kibbutz becomes more efficient.", "sol": -5.0, "pop": 0.0, "answerBonusValue": -5.0, "econ": 10.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Give power to smaller committees"}, {"answerBonusVariable": "sol", "answerIdeology": "Religious", "rep": 0.0, "reply": "Consensus is a long and arduous process but it makes your members happier. One family leaves due to the long meetings. ", "sol": 5.0, "pop": -5.0, "answerBonusValue": -10.0, "econ": -5.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Develop a system of consensus decision-making."}, {"answerBonusVariable": "rep", "answerIdeology": "Socialist", "rep": 10.0, "reply": "Your founders are proud that the kibbutz retains the spirit of direct democracy at the Assembly. Younger members stop coming to the tedious meetings.", "sol": -10.0, "pop": 0.0, "answerBonusValue": 5.0, "econ": 0.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Retain direct democracy."}], "type": "I", "hook": "\"The tyranny of the majority must be broken!\""}, {"text": "Jewish paramilitary forces stockpile arms to defend against Arab attacks. A unit caches rifles and explosives in your kibbutz. A squad of British soldiers arrives at your gates looking for contraband weapons. \n\n\"We are looking for radicals and terrorists who threaten the peace in Palestine,\" says the officer.\n\nWhat do you tell them?", "answers": [{"answerBonusVariable": "sol", "answerIdeology": "Labor Zionist", "rep": -5.0, "reply": "The Jewish underground is unimpressed that you gave away their weapons so easily. But the British authorities reward you by expediting your farm exports. ", "sol": 0.0, "pop": 0.0, "answerBonusValue": -10.0, "econ": 5.0, "trig": "", "answer": "You were forced to hide the weapons and the British can take them."}, {"answerBonusVariable": "rep", "answerIdeology": "Religious", "rep": 5.0, "reply": "The risky ruse works. The British search but don't find the weapons hidden in the children's house. The Jewish underground thank you for your loyalty.", "sol": 0.0, "pop": 0.0, "answerBonusValue": 5.0, "econ": 0.0, "trig": "", "answer": "They are welcome to search your peaceful kibbutz."}, {"answerBonusVariable": "rep", "answerIdeology": "Labor Zionist", "rep": 10.0, "reply": "The British forces try to enter your gates and there is an exchange of rifle fire. Several members are killed but the British soldiers retreat. The legend of your bravery spreads through the Jewish underground.", "sol": 0.0, "pop": -5.0, "answerBonusValue": 10.0, "econ": -5.0, "trig": "", "answer": "The soldiers are trespassers and you will defend your kibbutz with force."}], "type": "E", "hook": "\"We need to search your kibbutz!\""}, {"text": "Several young members want to join the Palmach forces and train as part of the Jewish resistance. \n\n\"We want to be sent to Europe to fight the Nazis,\" says Gideon, a young volunteer.\n\nWhat do you tell them?", "answers": [{"answerBonusVariable": "sol", "answerIdeology": "Labor Zionist", "rep": -5.0, "reply": "They reluctantly stay on the kibbutz but aren't happy to miss a chance to be heroes. With news of the Holocaust, many kibbutzniks wonder if they could have done more to save their fellow Jews.", "sol": -5.0, "pop": 5.0, "answerBonusValue": -5.0, "econ": 5.0, "trig": "", "answer": "They should stay. Palestine and the kibbutz need them more than Europe."}, {"answerBonusVariable": "rep", "answerIdeology": "Labor Zionist", "rep": 5.0, "reply": "You let the young members train with the British. One young woman is sent behind enemy lines in Hungary, where she is captured, tortured and killed by the Nazis. Your kibbutz grieves, but her bravery inspires generations of Jews in the dark years of the Holocaust and afterwards. ", "sol": 0.0, "pop": -2.0, "answerBonusValue": 5.0, "econ": -5.0, "trig": "", "answer": "They can join the resistance and leave for Europe with your blessing"}], "type": "I", "hook": "\"Someone must fight the Nazi threat.\""}, {"text": "Across Palestine, riots and attacks pits Arabs and Jews against each other. \n\n\"The British forces should suppress the Arab uprising,\" says Moishe.\n\n\"We must work for equality in a future Jewish state,\" argues Yosef. \n\nOther members say any state in Palestine must be bi-national. \"A republic of the working people!\" insists Sarah.\n\n What should your kibbutz do about the \"Arab question\"?", "answers": [{"answerBonusVariable": "sol", "answerIdeology": "Socialist", "rep": -5.0, "reply": "Your kibbutz joins the majority of other settlements in focusing on the growth of your community and the future Jewish state. But resentment percolates in the villages beyond your gates.", "sol": 0.0, "pop": 5.0, "answerBonusValue": -5.0, "econ": 5.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Demand that British forces deal with the violence."}, {"answerBonusVariable": "rep", "answerIdeology": "Marxist", "rep": 5.0, "reply": "Your bold words are at odds with many other Jewish immigrants to Palestine. You hope your Arab neighbours know that you support their citizenship within a future state. Tensions persist.", "sol": 0.0, "pop": 0.0, "answerBonusValue": 10.0, "econ": 0.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Argue for equal rights in a future Jewish state."}, {"answerBonusVariable": "sol", "answerIdeology": "Labor Zionist", "rep": 10.0, "reply": "Many other Jewish colonists consider such a bi-national vision as impossible, even wrong. Not all of your members agree either. But you persist and invite Arab villagers to break bread in your home. ", "sol": -5.0, "pop": -5.0, "answerBonusValue": -5.0, "econ": 0.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Lobby your leaders for a bi-national Arab-Jewish state."}], "type": "E", "hook": "\"There must be peace between Arab and Jew!\""}, {"text": "The whole world is suffering under the Great Depression. The Jewish settlements in Palestine are no different. A kibbutz in your federation is struggling, on the verge of failure, and begs for help. \n\n\"We must help our comrades!\" argues Sarah. \n\nWhat can your kibbutz offer?", "answers": [{"answerBonusVariable": "rep", "answerIdeology": "Religious", "rep": 5.0, "reply": "The loan helps for a time, but the other kibbutz falters and never repays the debt. You are proud to support your fellow pioneers, but now you have debts to pay, too.", "sol": -5.0, "pop": 0.0, "answerBonusValue": 5.0, "econ": -10.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Give them a long-term loan."}, {"answerBonusVariable": "rep", "answerIdeology": "Socialist", "rep": 5.0, "reply": "Sending members keeps the ailing kibbutz afloat. You hope they will pay your generosity back if your community ever falters.", "sol": 0.0, "pop": -5.0, "answerBonusValue": 5.0, "econ": 0.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Send some members as workers and advisors."}, {"answerBonusVariable": "sol", "answerIdeology": "Marxist", "rep": -5.0, "reply": "The other kibbutzgoes bankrupt. Several members move into your community. Other pioneers question your community's commitment to mutual aid. ", "sol": 0.0, "pop": 10.0, "answerBonusValue": -5.0, "econ": 5.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Tell them you can't afford to help right now."}], "type": "E", "hook": "\"Alas, we have nothing more to give!\""}, {"text": "A trio of Jewish guerrilla fighters arrive at your kibbutz in the middle night and ask to be hidden from the authorities. The next morning, British soldiers arrive. \n\n\"We're looking for terrorists from the Irgun,\" an officer demands. \"They sabotaged a convoy and killed one of our men.\" \n\nWhat do you tell them?", "answers": [{"answerBonusVariable": "rep", "answerIdeology": "Labor Zionist", "rep": 5.0, "reply": "The soldiers believe your lie. The next day you help the guerrillas escape to their HQ in a farm truck. The leaders of the Jewish resistance will remember your bravery.", "sol": 5.0, "pop": 0.0, "answerBonusValue": 5.0, "econ": 0.0, "trig": "", "answer": "You've seen no evidence of Jewish resistance fighters."}, {"answerBonusVariable": "sol", "answerIdeology": "Labor Zionist", "rep": -5.0, "reply": "The British sweep the kibbutz. They spot the guerrillas fleeing out the back gate and arrest two. Several get away.", "sol": 5.0, "pop": 0.0, "answerBonusValue": -10.0, "econ": 0.0, "trig": "", "answer": "You are a neutral kibbutz but they can search your grounds."}, {"answerBonusVariable": "sol", "answerIdeology": "Labor Zionist", "rep": -10.0, "reply": "The British shackle the Jewish guerrillas and reward your honesty. After a short trial, the leaders are sentenced to be hanged for treason. Your kibbutz remains blackened in the memories of Jewish partisans.", "sol": 0.0, "pop": 0.0, "answerBonusValue": -10.0, "econ": 5.0, "trig": "", "answer": "You reveal the hiding location of the guerrilla fighters."}], "type": "I", "hook": "\"We are peaceful kibbutzniks who would do you no harm!\""}, {"text": "The kibbutz needs to expand outward, but members disagree how to redesign the community.\n\n\"We must be ready to defend our village,\" says Itzik.  \"Let's add a tower and a stockade and a fence to protect the community.\"\n\n\"No,\" says Sarah. \"Let's add a dining hall in the centre with rings of housing around it to promote community.\"\n\nWhat do you suggest?", "answers": [{"answerBonusVariable": "sol", "answerIdeology": "Socialist", "rep": 5.0, "reply": "The traditional fort-style kibbutz provides a sense of security, even if accommodations are cramped. Your reputation grows as an outpost on the hinterland of Palestine.", "sol": 0.0, "pop": 0.0, "answerBonusValue": -5.0, "econ": -5.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Add a tower and stockade for defense."}, {"answerBonusVariable": "sol", "answerIdeology": "Socialist", "rep": 0.0, "reply": "Your borrow a master plan from the Garden City movement. The new design funnels members into the centre of the kibbutz for meals, celebrations, debates and other shared activities. ", "sol": 5.0, "pop": 5.0, "answerBonusValue": 5.0, "econ": -5.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Use a circular master plan."}], "type": "E", "hook": "\"First we shape our buildings and then they shape us!\""}]}, {"newEra": {"sol": 0.0, "type": "newEra", "rep": 0.0, "text": "The war ends with the defeat of Nazi Germany.  You slowly learn of the true horrors of the Holocaust. The European youth movements that supplied the kibbutzim with volunteers have been exterminated among the 6 million lost in the Shoah. \n\nCan anybody deny the need for a nation for the decimated Jewish people? You hear rumours that the new United Nations wants to turn part of Palestine into a Jewish state. You hope your kibbutz will one day mark the borders of this nation. \n\nAnd so you prepare to defend it...", "pop": 1.5, "hook": "1946-1955: Birth of a Nation", "econ": 1.5}, "questions": [{"text": "The British authorities restrict immigration from Jewish Holocaust survivors to Palestine. These refugees are smuggled across the borders anyway. Some are captured and held in a coastal detention camp. Most of your members fear there is little you can do.\n\n\"Let's take action!\" demands Itzik, a member of the Jewish militia.\n\nWhat do you suggest?", "answers": [{"answerBonusVariable": "rep", "answerIdeology": "Religious", "rep": -5.0, "reply": "Your protests fall on deaf ears. Kept in transit camps, many refugees die of diseases in their weakened state. You wish you had done more.", "sol": -5.0, "pop": 0.0, "answerBonusValue": 10.0, "econ": 0.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Protest the detentions to the British authorities."}, {"answerBonusVariable": "rep", "answerIdeology": "Labor Zionist", "rep": 5.0, "reply": "It's a risky venture. Several members are arrested during the action. But a large group of refugees slip through the British blockade into Palestine. ", "sol": 0.0, "pop": 5.0, "answerBonusValue": 5.0, "econ": -5.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Send your bravest members to coordinate a rescue operation."}], "type": "E", "hook": "\"We must rescue the refugees!\""}, {"text": "Jewish leaders in Palestine prepare for possible independence. Several of your most ambitious members want to join the cause as military and political leaders in Tel Aviv. But other members worry about the impact of a \"brain drain\" on your economy and community. \n\n\"Our kibbutz can only remain strong if we stay together,\" warns Shmuel.\n\nWhat do you suggest?", "answers": [{"answerBonusVariable": "sol", "answerIdeology": "Marxist", "rep": 10.0, "reply": "It's difficult to fill leadership positions on your kibbutz after your most ambitious members leave. The kibbutz economy suffers, but your members' political workmakes you all proud. ", "sol": 0.0, "pop": -5.0, "answerBonusValue": -5.0, "econ": -5.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Allow your members to join Jewish leaders in Tel Aviv."}, {"answerBonusVariable": "rep", "answerIdeology": "Labor Zionist", "rep": 0.0, "reply": "One of your ambitious members complains his efforts to help the country have been thwarted. Still, the extra hands result in a bumper crop.", "sol": -5.0, "pop": 5.0, "answerBonusValue": -5.0, "econ": 10.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Ask your members to stay and defend the kibbutz."}], "type": "E", "hook": "\"Go to Tel Aviv and lead us to independence!\"\""}, {"text": "The Partition Plan would divide Palestine into a jigsaw-puzzle of Arab and Jewish quadrants. Your settlement falls within the proposed Jewish territory and will define its future border. The Jewish government-in-waiting supports the plan. Leaders of Arab nations reject it. Your kibbutz members aren't 100% sure.\n\n\"We won't get a better deal,\" says Hannah. \n\nMoishe and Shlomo lament: \"Greater Israel should never be divided!\"\n\nWhat do you tell the Assembly? ", "answers": [{"answerBonusVariable": "rep", "answerIdeology": "Labor Zionist", "rep": 5.0, "reply": "Your members rally behind the prospect of a state for the Jewish people. New immigrants join your community as pioneers.", "sol": 0.0, "pop": 1.25, "answerBonusValue": -10.0, "econ": 1.25, "trig": "", "answer": "Tell Jewish leaders to accept the deal."}, {"answerBonusVariable": "rep", "answerIdeology": "Religious", "rep": -10.0, "reply": "Your members think the Partition Plan is a raw deal for the Jewish people. You hope that colonial powers will reconsider the flawed plan and give more land to your people.", "sol": 5.0, "pop": 0.0, "answerBonusValue": 20.0, "econ": 5.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Tell Jewish leaders to fight for more of the Promised Land."}, {"answerBonusVariable": "rep", "answerIdeology": "Marxist", "rep": 0.0, "reply": "Speaking out against partition is a bold move that sets your kibbutz at odds with the leaders of Jewish independence. But you believe a land divided will never live in peace.", "sol": -5.0, "pop": 0.0, "answerBonusValue": 20.0, "econ": -5.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Insist on a single, undivided, bi-national state. Or no state at all."}], "type": "E", "hook": "\"Are we giving up too much?\""}, {"text": "During the 1948 War, Arab villagers flee past your kibbutz. Their children are crying in the wagons outside your gates. \n\n\"They will be safer in Lebanon and Jordan,\" says Moishe.\n\nWhat do tell the villagers?", "answers": [{"answerBonusVariable": "sol", "answerIdeology": "Marxist", "rep": -5.0, "reply": "The villagers continue toward neighbouring Arab states. After the war, you never see your former neighbours again, as they aren't allowed to return. You inherit several of their farm fields and olive orchards.", "sol": 0.0, "pop": 0.0, "answerBonusValue": 0.75, "econ": 1.5, "trig": "", "answer": "They should flee to safety in an Arab nation."}, {"answerBonusVariable": "rep", "answerIdeology": "Religious", "rep": 5.0, "reply": "The fleeing villagers thank you for your generosity and disappear toward the horizon. ", "sol": 0.0, "pop": 0.0, "answerBonusValue": 10.0, "econ": -5.0, "trig": "", "answer": "You offer food and money and promise to watch over their village until they return."}, {"answerBonusVariable": "sol", "answerIdeology": "Labor Zionist", "rep": 10.0, "reply": "Some of the villagers take up your offer of sanctuary. The Army arrives and marches the villagers to a larger Arab town. They are never allowed to return to their original village, but they become citizens in the new state of Israel and pay back your generosity by working for hire when you need extra hands.", "sol": -5.0, "pop": 0.0, "answerBonusValue": 0.75, "econ": 10.0, "trig": "", "answer": "You let them stay in your kibbutz until the the fighting is over."}], "type": "E", "hook": "\"We can't protect them when the Army arrives...\""}, {"text": "In 1948, Arab legionnaires lay siege to the kibbutz with tanks and cannons. After several days, their forces nearly overrun the perimeter fence. You are running low on food and ammunition. \n\n\"Defenders of the frontier must never surrender!\" says Itzik \n\n\"Ah, that's fool's talk!\" replies Yosef. \"We must live to fight another day.\"\n\nWhat do you do? ", "answers": [{"answerBonusVariable": "rep", "answerIdeology": "Labor Zionist", "rep": 10.0, "reply": "Several members die in the battle. More are killed when Arab legionnaires overrun your kibbutz. You are captured and your buildings razed. But when you are released after the war, the legend of your valiant stand resonates across the new nation.", "sol": 5.0, "pop": 0.75, "answerBonusValue": 20.0, "econ": 0.75, "trig": "", "answer": "Remain and defend the kibbutz till the end."}, {"answerBonusVariable": "rep", "answerIdeology": "Religious", "rep": 5.0, "reply": "David Ben-Gurion reluctantly acquiesces to your demands for help. Several kibbutzniks die in the battle, but you hold on until cannons and fresh militia can arrive. Your defense of your kibbutz becomes part of your nation's founding myth.", "sol": 0.0, "pop": 0.8, "answerBonusValue": 5.0, "econ": 0.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Evacuate the women and children and send an emissary to Tel Aviv to beg for reinforcements."}, {"answerBonusVariable": "rep", "answerIdeology": "Labor Zionist", "rep": -10.0, "reply": "The Arab forces sweep through your abandoned kibbutz. Eventually, the Jewish army pushes them back and you return home. You share little of the glory of other kibbutzniks who defended their territory. ", "sol": -10.0, "pop": 5.0, "answerBonusValue": 0.5, "econ": -5.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Abandon the kibbutz and retreat."}], "type": "E", "hook": "\"It's over! Our enemies are at our gates!\""}, {"text": "Your kibbutz acquires farmland abandoned by Palestinian farmers who fled to Lebanon or Jordan. Your members argue about how to best use this property.\n\n\"Taking their land makes me uncomfortable,\" says Dudu.\n\nWhat do you do with the land? ", "answers": [{"answerBonusVariable": "rep", "answerIdeology": "Marxist", "rep": 1.25, "reply": "The decision to leave the Arab tenants' fields untilled divides your members, but ideology wins out over economics. The grown-over fields and olive orchards remind future generations that you once hoped to share this land.", "sol": 0.75, "pop": -5.0, "answerBonusValue": 10.0, "econ": 0.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Leave it untouched."}, {"answerBonusVariable": "rep", "answerIdeology": "Socialist", "rep": 5.0, "reply": "The park proves popular with members and locals. Tourists from the city camp on weekends and buy supplies in your general store.", "sol": 0.0, "pop": 0.0, "answerBonusValue": 10.0, "econ": 10.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Turn it into a park."}, {"answerBonusVariable": "rep", "answerIdeology": "Marxist", "rep": 0.0, "reply": "You join dozens of kibbutzniks in farming abandoned fields. Within a few years, most of your members forget who once owned this land. ", "sol": 5.0, "pop": 5.0, "answerBonusValue": 0.75, "econ": 1.5, "trig": "", "answer": "Cultivate the land for agriculture."}, {"answerBonusVariable": "pop", "answerIdeology": "Labor Zionist", "rep": -5.0, "reply": "The decision to build so quickly on abandoned land raises question in your kibbutz federation. But roomier quarters attract a new wave of workers to your community.", "sol": 5.0, "pop": 10.0, "answerBonusValue": 1.25, "econ": 10.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Use the land to build new apartments. "}], "type": "E", "hook": "\"The kibbutz needs to expand!\""}, {"text": "An ideological schism splits the kibbutz movement. Some members believe in the Soviet philosophy of state socialism. Others want to distance the kibbutz from the USSR. Arguments erupt in the General Assembly. Members stop talking to each other.\n\n\"If we can't agree,\" says Miriam, one of your founders, \"we must split the kibbutz in two!\"\n\nWhat do you suggest?", "answers": [{"answerBonusVariable": "sol", "answerIdeology": "Marxist", "rep": 0.8, "reply": "Alas, the two sides refuse to talk to each other. Several families leave. The rest avoid each other in the dining hall and at work. The feud lasts for years and poisons the mood of your community.", "sol": -10.0, "pop": 0.75, "answerBonusValue": -10.0, "econ": 0.8, "trig": "", "answer": "Try to resolve the differences between the groups."}, {"answerBonusVariable": "rep", "answerIdeology": "Religious", "rep": 5.0, "reply": "A small core of ideologues leaves the kibbutz. Your division heals faster than on other split kibbutzes so you can focus on more productive issues than the virtues of Soviet Russia.", "sol": -5.0, "pop": 0.9, "answerBonusValue": 10.0, "econ": 0.9, "trig": "", "answer": "Try to split amicably and cooperate."}, {"answerBonusVariable": "sol", "answerIdeology": "Labor Zionist", "rep": 1.25, "reply": "The debate becomes an all-out battle for control of the kibbutz. A line of barbed wire is strung across the dining room. Finally, a large group of members secedes to form their own kibbutz. It takes years before members of the two adjacent kibbutzim talk to each other again.", "sol": 0.0, "pop": 0.6, "answerBonusValue": -10.0, "econ": 0.75, "trig": "", "answer": "Make a hard split and go your separate ways."}], "type": "B", "hook": "\"Are you for the International Revolution or a tool of capitalist imperialists?\""}]}, {"newEra": {"sol": 0.0, "type": "newEra", "rep": 5.0, "text": "The kibbutz movement is renowned for its role in the creation and defense of the State of Israel. Your communities feed a rapidly expanding population from your fields and orchards. In a single generation, you have fulfilled Theodor Herzl's dream.\n\nBut you also imagined so much more: equality, fraternity, solidarity. Israel grows into a modern nation, with cities and development towns, religious enclaves and Arab quarters. A generation of kibbutz-born children become the new leaders who must define your community's future. \n\nWhat role should the kibbutz play in Israel's complex society? \n", "pop": 1.5, "hook": "1956-1965: Coming of Age", "econ": 10.0}, "questions": [{"text": "For years, a quiet kibbutznik has written novels in Hebrew that have become popular in Israel and even translated overseas. \n\n\"I'd like an extra day off from work to write my books,\" he says.\n\n\"Wouldn't we all!\" responds Shmuel.\n\nWhat do you recommend?", "answers": [{"answerBonusVariable": "sol", "answerIdeology": "Socialist", "rep": 10.0, "reply": "You lose some work hours, but the young author develops into one of your nation's most esteemed novelists, although not every member is happy about how he depicts kibbutz life. ", "sol": -5.0, "pop": 5.0, "answerBonusValue": -5.0, "econ": -5.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Allow him an extra day off."}, {"answerBonusVariable": "sol", "answerIdeology": "Socialist", "rep": 5.0, "reply": "The author is touched by the offer but declines the help of the elderly literary assistants. He develops a reputation as a talented storyteller on his ow -and your members feel proud to see his name on bestseller lists.", "sol": 0.0, "pop": 0.0, "answerBonusValue": 5.0, "econ": 0.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Give him no extra time off but assign older members to help research his books and increase literary productivity."}, {"answerBonusVariable": "rep", "answerIdeology": "Labor Zionist", "rep": -5.0, "reply": "The young author leaves the kibbutz with his family to write fill-time in the city. You later become known as the kibbutz that kicked out Israel's greatest novelist.", "sol": 5.0, "pop": -5.0, "answerBonusValue": -5.0, "econ": 5.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Give him no extra time off. Everybody must work the same rotation"}], "type": "I", "hook": "\"No, every kibbutznik must do the same work!\""}, {"text": "The government has negotiated reparations from West Germany as payment for Jewish slave labour and stolen property during the Holocaust. Your kibbutz, like the rest of the country, is divided about whether to accept this money. \n\n\"It belittles the atrocity of the Shoah,\" argues Hannah. \n\nYosef disagrees: \"We are a poor village in a poor country that has suffered enough...\"\n\nWhat do you recommend?", "answers": [{"answerBonusVariable": "sol", "answerIdeology": "Labor Zionist", "rep": 10.0, "reply": "Your rejection of the German reparations makes news throughout the country. You aren't a rich community, but your members are reminded that money corrupts and Nazi money corrupts absolutely.", "sol": -5.0, "pop": 0.0, "answerBonusValue": 10.0, "econ": 0.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Reject the reparations."}, {"answerBonusVariable": "rep", "answerIdeology": "Labor Zionist", "rep": 5.0, "reply": "You accept the reparation mopney and use it build a new wing for your old-age home and a library. This will help all your members never forget to never forget.", "sol": 5.0, "pop": 5.0, "answerBonusValue": -10.0, "econ": 10.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Take the reparations and use it to improve the whole kibbutz."}, {"answerBonusVariable": "rep", "answerIdeology": "Religious", "rep": 0.0, "reply": "You let the survivors keep the reparations. Some members grumble about extra benefits but don't share their opinions publicly.", "sol": -5.0, "pop": 5.0, "answerBonusValue": 10.0, "econ": 5.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Only let Holocaust survivors take the money."}], "type": "E", "hook": "\"We should never take blood money from Germany!\""}, {"text": "The new Jewish State welcomes hundreds of thousands of new immigrants every year. Many are poor Mizrahi Jews cast out from Arab countries in the wake of Israel's independence. Prime Minister David Ben Gurion demands that kibbutzniks do their part and absorb these immigrants as members. \n\n\"We need to only take members who understand our philosophy,\" cautions Shmuel.\n\nWhat do you recommend? ", "answers": [{"answerBonusVariable": "rep", "answerIdeology": "Labor Zionist", "rep": 5.0, "reply": "It's difficult at first to integrate the new arrivals, who are more religious and less educated. But they are hard workers who welcome a new home--and new homeland--after fleeing the Arab states. The Israeli government rewards you for helping with the mass influx of new citizens, unlike many of your fellow kibbutzniks, who shut their doors on these immgirants.", "sol": 0.75, "pop": 1.5, "answerBonusValue": 1.25, "econ": 1.5, "trig": "", "answer": "You accept a dozen new families from the Arab states."}, {"answerBonusVariable": "sol", "answerIdeology": "Socialist", "rep": -5.0, "reply": "You keep the new arrivals at a distance. They live in concrete apartments in new cities and commute by bus to work in your fields and factories. Your agricultural operations thrive with this cheap Jewish labour. A few immigrants marry into the kibbutz. ", "sol": 0.0, "pop": 10.0, "answerBonusValue": 0.8, "econ": 1.25, "trig": "", "answer": "You can't absorb new members but you will hire the immigrants as laborers and factory workers."}, {"answerBonusVariable": "sol", "answerIdeology": "Marxist", "rep": -10.0, "reply": "You maintain the ideological purity of your community but only accepting members from your youth movement. Outside your gates, the Mizrahi immigrants resent your luxuries and superior attitude.", "sol": 5.0, "pop": 5.0, "answerBonusValue": 10.0, "econ": 5.0, "trig": "", "answer": "You only accept members from your own youth movement. "}], "type": "E", "hook": "\"Our kibbutz can't absorb so many new members!\""}, {"text": "Several members want the kibbutz to invest more time and money into improving the gardens around residences. \n\n\"We must create our own Eden,\" says Dudu, a young gardener.\n\n\"Bah!\" argues Gideon, a soldier. \"We have more important needs.\"\n\nThe idea will be put to a vote. ", "answers": [{"answerBonusVariable": "sol", "answerIdeology": "Marxist", "rep": 10.0, "reply": "A garden committee establishes flower beds and scented bushes throughout the kibbutz. Your community becomes known as the \"Eden on the frontier.\" Pride blooms in the heart of everyone who lives there, even if it comes at a price. ", "sol": 5.0, "pop": 5.0, "answerBonusValue": -10.0, "econ": -5.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Support the gardens to beautify your community."}, {"answerBonusVariable": "sol", "answerIdeology": "Marxist", "rep": 0.0, "reply": "You invest profits back into your fields and factory. Your economy grows. But the austere living conditions take a toll on members. Several leave.", "sol": -5.0, "pop": -5.0, "answerBonusValue": 10.0, "econ": 10.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Say no to an ornamental garden. Basic needs must be met first."}], "type": "I", "hook": "\"What next? White picket fences!?\""}, {"text": "At the Assembly, a debate breaks out about where to re-invest profits to help grow the kibbutz.\n\n\"It's time to industrialize,\" argues Amos. \n\n\"No,\" counters Miriam, \"we came to Palestine to work the land.\"\n\nWhere should you focus your resources?\n", "answers": [{"answerBonusVariable": "rep", "answerIdeology": "Socialist", "rep": 5.0, "reply": "You expand your agricultural operations. New equipment and imported techniques result in even better crops. ", "sol": 0.0, "pop": 0.0, "answerBonusValue": 10.0, "econ": 1.25, "trig": "", "answer": "Buy more farming equipment."}, {"answerBonusVariable": "sol", "answerIdeology": "Religious", "rep": 10.0, "reply": "Nobody complains about investing in the kibbutz's new generation. And the expanded school draws students from surrounding communities as well as new members..", "sol": 5.0, "pop": 1.5, "answerBonusValue": 5.0, "econ": 0.8, "trig": "", "answer": "Improve the children's quarters and school."}, {"answerBonusVariable": "rep", "answerIdeology": "Labor Zionist", "rep": 0.0, "reply": "It's costly to expand living quarters for every member. Still, the new space improves everyone's work ethic and even draws new pioneers to take up membership. The frontier is tough but it doesn't have to be claustrophobic  ", "sol": 5.0, "pop": 1.25, "answerBonusValue": 10.0, "econ": 0.75, "trig": "", "answer": "Expand everyone's living quarters."}, {"answerBonusVariable": "sol", "answerIdeology": "Socialist", "rep": 0.0, "reply": "Your kibbutz federation helps to fund a new factory, which pays dividends and attracts new members to work there on the line or as managers. Some founders worry you are moving away from their philosophy of working the land.", "sol": -5.0, "pop": 5.0, "answerBonusValue": -5.0, "econ": 1.5, "trig": "", "answer": "Add a factory."}], "type": "E", "hook": "\"We can't stay farmers forever!\""}, {"text": "Your founders have grown too old for field work but still want to contribute rather than retire. \n\n\"We could add a factory where shifts would be easier on their bodies than farming,\" suggests Ziva.\n\nWhat do you do about your elderly members?", "answers": [{"answerBonusVariable": "sol", "answerIdeology": "Labor Zionist", "rep": 5.0, "reply": "The founders don't complain. They are used to hard work and are happy to do what they can to contribute to the kibbutz. A few decide to leave for an easier life in the city.", "sol": 0.0, "pop": -5.0, "answerBonusValue": 0.8, "econ": 5.0, "trig": "", "answer": "They still must work but fewer hours."}, {"answerBonusVariable": "sol", "answerIdeology": "Marxist", "rep": 10.0, "reply": "It's a costly investment to build a retirement home. But visiting their parents and grandparents deepens each members' connection to the community and its history.", "sol": 5.0, "pop": 5.0, "answerBonusValue": 0.75, "econ": 0.75, "trig": "", "answer": "Expand the seniors home for the new retirees."}, {"answerBonusVariable": "rep", "answerIdeology": "Religious", "rep": -5.0, "reply": "Your founders are happy to contribute to the kibbutz economy, even though they can't work in the fields. \"Retirement is for capitalists!\" they say with a sly smile.", "sol": 5.0, "pop": 5.0, "answerBonusValue": -5.0, "econ": 1.25, "trig": "", "answer": "Build a small factory where they can work."}, {"answerBonusVariable": "rep", "answerIdeology": "Socialist", "rep": -5.0, "reply": "Moving your older generation to the nearby city makes sense but nobody is happy with the result. The founders feel disconnected from the community they built. And other kibbutzniks think you have abandoned your ideals.", "sol": -5.0, "pop": -5.0, "answerBonusValue": -5.0, "econ": 5.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Let them retire in a seniors' home in town."}], "type": "E", "hook": "\"Only work gives meaning to life!\""}, {"text": "A rumour circulates that Nir, a handsome bachelor kibbutznik, has been flirting (and perhaps more) with kibbutz wives when their husbands are away in the Army. You're not sure what is truth and what's rumour. \n\n\"We must discuss this at the General Assembly!\" says Moishe, who suspects Nir of trying to entice his wife. \n\nWhat do you do about the situation?", "answers": [{"answerBonusVariable": "sol", "answerIdeology": "Labor Zionist", "rep": 5.0, "reply": "Everyone welcomes the chance to air their gossip at the next meeting and to hear other people's rumours. Except for Nir. He decides to leave the kibbutz for someplace more private.", "sol": 5.0, "pop": -5.0, "answerBonusValue": -10.0, "econ": 0.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Add \"Nir's Flirtations\" to the agenda for the next meeting."}, {"answerBonusVariable": "rep", "answerIdeology": "Religious", "rep": 0.0, "reply": "Nir gets the message and keeps his romancing more discreet. Eventually, he marries a members from the next kibbutz and they raise a family in your community. ", "sol": 0.0, "pop": 5.0, "answerBonusValue": 10.0, "econ": 5.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Tell Nir to control his behaviour or he will be on permanent dishwasher duty."}, {"answerBonusVariable": "rep", "answerIdeology": "Socialist", "rep": 5.0, "reply": "Nir stays. The gossip about his clandestine love life doesn't disappear. And kibbutz men grumble about the Lothario in their midst. Over the next few years, the kibbutz experiences a mini baby boom", "sol": -5.0, "pop": 5.0, "answerBonusValue": 5.0, "econ": 0.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Ignore the rumours. Your members are adults who can do what they want."}], "type": "I", "hook": "\"Did you hear about Nir and Moishe's wife?\""}]}, {"newEra": {"sol": 0.0, "type": "newEra", "rep": 10.0, "text": "Your nation teeters on the brink of another war with the surrounding Arab nations. Your members are called to arms. And then in a flash, Israel emerges victorious. Many of the heroes of the Six Dar War grew up as kibbutzniks. Many casualties, too.\n\nBut you face new questions. How do you adjust to the changing society around you? How do you make peace with the Arab nations you defeated? And what about a new generation of pioneers who want settle the captured territories?", "pop": 1.25, "hook": "1965-1975: The Six Day War and its Aftermath", "econ": 1.25}, "questions": [{"text": "An American psychologist wants to stay on your kibbutz and study the effects of communal child-rearing on the community's socio-dynamics. He promises not to name your kibbutz when he publishes the results.\n\n\"We have nothing to hide,\" says Tonya, the nanny. \"The world should know about our way of life!\" Other members worry about the intrusion.\n\nDo you allow the scholar to live on your kibbutz for his research?", "answers": [{"answerBonusVariable": "rep", "answerIdeology": "Socialist", "rep": -5.0, "reply": "You miss a shot at fame, but who cares? You don't need a glorified shrink to say you're special ", "sol": 0.0, "pop": 0.0, "answerBonusValue": -10.0, "econ": 0.0, "trig": "", "answer": "No. Your privacy is more important."}, {"answerBonusVariable": "rep", "answerIdeology": "Socialist", "rep": 10.0, "reply": "Some members are uncomfortable with the questions, but the book goes on to become a landmark study in child psychology. You feel honoured to display the unique way of child-rearing at the kibbutz.", "sol": -5.0, "pop": 0.0, "answerBonusValue": 10.0, "econ": 0.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Yes. As long your identity remains anonymous."}, {"answerBonusVariable": "sol", "answerIdeology": "Religious", "rep": 20.0, "reply": "Tthe academic study becomes a bestseller. People around the world learn about the Israeli communal movement through life on your one small village. Membership goes up along with your reputation.", "sol": -5.0, "pop": 1.25, "answerBonusValue": -5.0, "econ": 5.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Yes. Your community is a true utopia and the world should know this."}], "type": "I", "hook": " \"What are we, fish in a fish bowl?\""}, {"text": "Parents in your kibbutz want their children to sleep in their apartments rather than in the communal children's house with the nanny. \n\n\"We can use the children's houses for daycares or workshops,\" says Amos. \n\nOlder members worry this will end the kibbutz's unique way of educating children. \"It will be the end of the communal spirit!\" warns Moishe.\n\nThe General Assembly has never been this divided. What do you recommend?", "answers": [{"answerBonusVariable": "sol", "answerIdeology": "Marxist", "rep": 0.75, "reply": "The move makes most members happy. They always wanted more time with the children. Other kibbutzes wonder if you are even really a kibbutz any more. The kids keep being kids...", "sol": 5.0, "pop": 10.0, "answerBonusValue": -15.0, "econ": -10.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Let children sleep in their parents' apartments."}, {"answerBonusVariable": "sol", "answerIdeology": "Labor Zionist", "rep": 1.5, "reply": "A few families leave. Keeping the chldren's house reinforces your reputation as the vanguard of creating the New Jew and lets parents socialize in the evenings.", "sol": 0.0, "pop": -5.0, "answerBonusValue": -10.0, "econ": 10.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Retain the children's houses for communal child-rearing."}], "type": "B", "hook": "\"Only the nanny can train good kibbtuzniks!\""}, {"text": "Years ago, your kibbutz debated the \"dangers\" of letting members keep a tea kettle in their rooms. Now members request private TVs in rather than share one communal set.\n\n\"Are they too proud to watch in the dining hall with the rest of us?\" complains Moishe, one of your founders.\n\nWhat do you decide? ", "answers": [{"answerBonusVariable": "sol", "answerIdeology": "Marxist", "rep": -5.0, "reply": "Members welcome the chance to own their own TVs. But attendance at the General Assembly and even social events suffers. ", "sol": -5.0, "pop": 10.0, "answerBonusValue": 0.75, "econ": 0.75, "trig": "", "answer": "Buy all members their own private TVs."}, {"answerBonusVariable": "sol", "answerIdeology": "Socialist", "rep": 5.0, "reply": "The TV room become the new gathering hub. Kibbutzniks wander in to watch the news or a favourite show and chat with their neighbhours. ", "sol": 5.0, "pop": 0.0, "answerBonusValue": 5.0, "econ": -5.0, "trig": "", "answer": "No private TVs but buy new colour units for the dining hall, the card room and old-age home."}, {"answerBonusVariable": "rep", "answerIdeology": "Marxist", "rep": 10.0, "reply": "People in the city are amazed by how your kibbutz rejects modern entertainment, and several families leave. But there are plenty of social activities in your community to keep the remaining members happy.", "sol": -5.0, "pop": -5.0, "answerBonusValue": 1.25, "econ": 0.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Get rid of the one TV you have."}], "type": "I", "hook": "\"Go live in the city if you need an idiot box!\""}, {"text": "Terror strikes the kibbutz. Palestinian fedayeen fighters infiltrate the perimeter fence and kill three members.  Your sense of security feels violated.\n\n\"We must track down the infiltrators and make them pay!\" shouts Itzik, a veteran commando. \n\n\"No,\" cautions Hannah. \"Let the Army protect us from future attacks.\" \n\nHow do you respond? ", "answers": [{"answerBonusVariable": "sol", "answerIdeology": "Socialist", "rep": 1.5, "reply": "Two young members die in a firefight when they corner the fedayeen. Your kibbutz makes headlines as the home of martyrs for defending the nation against terrorism.", "sol": 5.0, "pop": -5.0, "answerBonusValue": -10.0, "econ": 0.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Send younger kibbutzniks to track down the terrorists."}, {"answerBonusVariable": "sol", "answerIdeology": "Labor Zionist", "rep": -5.0, "reply": "The Army increases patrols and you focus on getting your crops to market. Some old-timers think you should have sought revenge. ", "sol": -5.0, "pop": 5.0, "answerBonusValue": -5.0, "econ": 10.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Demand extra protection from the IDF."}, {"answerBonusVariable": "sol", "answerIdeology": "Marxist", "rep": 0.0, "reply": "The defenses calm members' worries. New kibbutzniks take comfort in the barbed wire and scrutiny at the gate. It's a reality across the country: security must come before peace.", "sol": 5.0, "pop": 10.0, "answerBonusValue": -10.0, "econ": -5.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Reinforce the perimeter fence and re-assign two workers to 24/7 guard duty."}], "type": "E", "hook": "\"Only revenge will do!\""}, {"text": "After the  victory of the Six Day War, your federation wants to build a new kibbutz in the Occupied Territories and asks for help. \n\n\"These are the new pioneers of Greater Israel!\" says Yoav, a young member. \"I want to join!\"\n\n\"Are you crazy?\" says Miriam. \"These new settlers will ruin our country!\"\n\nDo you support the decision to build a kibbutz in the Occupied Territories?", "answers": [{"answerBonusVariable": "sol", "answerIdeology": "Marxist", "rep": -5.0, "reply": "Several of your members leave to help establish the new outpost. The government helps to subsidize their enterprise. The Occupation of the Palestinian Territories will become a thorny issue and will tarnish your reputation.", "sol": 0.0, "pop": -5.0, "answerBonusValue": 0.75, "econ": 10.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Send members as workers and advisors."}, {"answerBonusVariable": "rep", "answerIdeology": "Religious", "rep": -5.0, "reply": "Your kibbutz watches from afar as the new settlements appear in the Occupied Territories. You envy their pioneering spirit but less so when Palestinians resist the settlers in their midst.", "sol": 0.0, "pop": 0.0, "answerBonusValue": 2.5, "econ": 5.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Support in principle but focus on your own operations."}, {"answerBonusVariable": "sol", "answerIdeology": "Religious", "rep": 5.0, "reply": "In the years to come, you will realize you were right: the settlements have caused more pain and problems for Israel. But what is done is done.", "sol": 0.0, "pop": 0.0, "answerBonusValue": 0.5, "econ": 0.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Refuse any support."}, {"answerBonusVariable": "rep", "answerIdeology": "Marxist", "rep": 5.0, "reply": "It's hard to speak out against your own federation, but you send a delegation to warn of the dangers of establishing settlments on another people's land. ", "sol": -5.0, "pop": 0.0, "answerBonusValue": 1.5, "econ": -5.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Threaten to leave the federation if it builds a kibbutz in the Territories."}], "type": "E", "hook": "\"Yes, they are the new pioneers of Greater Israel!\""}, {"text": "An eccentric mechanic on your kibbutz invented an electric device to remove hair from women's legs. He asks the General Assembly to invest in a factory to mass-produce his invention. \n\n\"I've never heard of such folly!\" argues Moishe.\n\nWhat do you advise the kibbutz? ", "answers": [{"answerBonusVariable": "rep", "answerIdeology": "Marxist", "rep": 10.0, "reply": "Surprise! The electrical depilatory device is a huge international success. Your kibbutz earns a national reputation for innovation and your bank account is flush with cash. Everybody wants to be a member of the \"millionaire's kibbutz\".", "sol": -5.0, "pop": 1.25, "answerBonusValue": -20.0, "econ": 1.9, "trig": "", "answer": "Invest your reserve funds to build a factory and market the invention."}, {"answerBonusVariable": "sol", "answerIdeology": "Labor Zionist", "rep": 0.0, "reply": "Nobody complains about playing it cautious with the kibbutz's limited funds. But the inventor leaves and sells his invention to a private company for several million shekels. ", "sol": 0.0, "pop": -5.0, "answerBonusValue": -10.0, "econ": 0.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Reject using kibbutz money for the proposal."}], "type": "E", "hook": "\"Are you mad? Risk the kibbutz for a lady shaver?!\""}, {"text": "In the prelude and  ftermath of the Six Day War of 1967, many male members are called up to Army units. \n\n\"How will the work get done?\" wonders Ziva, who has been put in charge of managing the kibbutz economy. \n\nWhat do you suggest?", "answers": [{"answerBonusVariable": "rep", "answerIdeology": "Socialist", "rep": 5.0, "reply": "The kibbutz suffers from the loss of workers, but working together throughout the war brings the remaining members together. ", "sol": 5.0, "pop": -5.0, "answerBonusValue": 10.0, "econ": 0.8, "trig": "", "answer": "Make do and return to normal operations at the end of the conflict."}, {"answerBonusVariable": "rep", "answerIdeology": "Labor Zionist", "rep": 5.0, "reply": "An influx of patriotic Jews from the U.S. and Europe offer their help. Some stay for a few months. Others marry into the kibbutz. They spread the legend of the kibbutz around the world. ", "sol": 0.0, "pop": 1.25, "answerBonusValue": 1.5, "econ": 5.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Invite Jews from the Diaspora to work in the fields and factories."}, {"answerBonusVariable": "rep", "answerIdeology": "Religious", "rep": 0.0, "reply": "You welcome non-Jewish volunteers in great numbers. The extra labour helps at harvest time and as your factory expands. Old-timers resent the rowdy newcomers, though, with their loud music and funny-smelling cigarettes.", "sol": 0.75, "pop": 1.25, "answerBonusValue": -5.0, "econ": 1.25, "trig": "", "answer": "Throw open gates to foreign backpackers as temporary volunteers."}], "type": "E", "hook": "\"Throw open the gates to foreigners!\""}, {"text": "A kibbutznik named Uri, who fought in the Six Day War,  became disillusioned by the occupation of the West Bank and Gaza and joined several radical left-wing groups. The Israeli secret service arrested him after he visited Syria to meet with Palestinian leaders.\n\nIsraelis are outraged a kibbutznik may have spied against the country. Your kibbutz is named in news reports. Some bus drivers refuse to stop at your kibbutz. \n\nHow do you protect your reputation? ", "answers": [{"answerBonusVariable": "rep", "answerIdeology": "Labor Zionist", "rep": 0.0, "reply": "By disavowing Uri, your kibbutz avoids too much scrutiny. But members wonder if you betrayed the ideals of your founders and Uri's family leaves the community.", "sol": -5.0, "pop": -5.0, "answerBonusValue": 10.0, "econ": 0.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Issue a press release dismissing Uri as a member and condemning his actions."}, {"answerBonusVariable": "rep", "answerIdeology": "Marxist", "rep": -5.0, "reply": "The case becomes a national scandal and the name of your kibbutz is front and centre. Right-wing politicians call your members traitors. Your welcome Uri home when he is released from jail 10 years later.", "sol": 5.0, "pop": 5.0, "answerBonusValue": 1.5, "econ": -10.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Help his family pay for Uri's legal bills and welcome him back, even if he goes to jail."}], "type": "I", "hook": "\"Uri is a fool and we are all the victims of his delusions!\""}, {"text": "A group of women approach the executive to complain about their treatment on the kibbutz. \n\n\"But this is the most equal society in the world!\" says Itzik, the director of work programs.\n\n\"Yes, we all earn the same as everyone else,\" says Ziva, \"and yet we are only assigned to work in the kitchen or the children's house, as secretaries or shop clerks.\" \n\nHow do you address their concerns? ", "answers": [{"answerBonusVariable": "sol", "answerIdeology": "Socialist", "rep": -5.0, "reply": "\"Kibbutz democracy is bullshit!\" the women reply. Several families leave. Others stage a protest strike. ", "sol": 0.0, "pop": -5.0, "answerBonusValue": 0.75, "econ": 0.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Every member already has an equal vote. No change is necessary"}, {"answerBonusVariable": "rep", "answerIdeology": "Labor Zionist", "rep": 0.0, "reply": "The new committee is slow to accomplish much, but it does give female members an outlet for grievances. ", "sol": 5.0, "pop": 0.0, "answerBonusValue": -10.0, "econ": 0.0, "trig": "", "answer": "The problem needs more study. Establish a Women's Rights Committee."}, {"answerBonusVariable": "sol", "answerIdeology": "Religious", "rep": 5.0, "reply": "The proposal disturbs old-time members but gets attention across the country. You bring in a female business manager from another kibbutz. ", "sol": -5.0, "pop": 5.0, "answerBonusValue": 0.5, "econ": 5.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Insist the next financial manager and community director all be women."}], "type": "I", "hook": "\"Ladies, you already live in a perfectly equal society!\""}]}, {"newEra": {"sol": -5.0, "type": "newEra", "rep": -5.0, "text": "For nearly 30 years, Israel has been led by left-wing governments backed by your members. That ends in 1977. Menachem Begin and the Likud Party rise to power. They attract religious voters and new immigrants disenchanted with the establishment of Israel, including the kibbutz.\n\nThen a financial crisis sweeps Israel. Spiraling hyper-inflation and interest rates throw markets into turmoil. Debts balloon. Members worry the kibbutz can no longer provide a safety net in uncertain times...", "pop": 5.0, "hook": "1976-1985 Political and Economic Crisis", "econ": -10.0}, "questions": [{"text": "The kibbutz asks Yuval, a creative young kibbutznik, attend university in Haifa so he can become a teacher in the regional high school. \n\n\"I'd prefer to study art in Paris for a year,\" he replies and asks the kibbutz to pay his tuition.\n\nWhat do you tell him? ", "answers": [{"answerBonusVariable": "rep", "answerIdeology": "Labor Zionist", "rep": 5.0, "reply": "It costs money to send Yuval abroad and some members resent his special treatment. He returns and establishes a studio/ gallery on the kibbutz. His watercolours become famous throughout Israel.", "sol": -5.0, "pop": 5.0, "answerBonusValue": 5.0, "econ": -5.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Fund his art school tuition as long as he returns to the kibbutz."}, {"answerBonusVariable": "rep", "answerIdeology": "Marxist", "rep": 0.0, "reply": "Yuval reluctantly agrees to the plan. He teaches painting in the local high school for a few years until he grows disillusioned and leaves the kibbutz for Paris. ", "sol": 5.0, "pop": -5.0, "answerBonusValue": 5.0, "econ": 5.0, "trig": "", "answer": "He can study art part-time in Haifa while he gets his teacher's training. "}], "type": "I", "hook": "\"The kibbutz needs teachers not painters!\""}, {"text": "Menachem Begin, the leader of the right-wing Likud Party and new Premier of Israel, gives a speech in which he describes \"kibbutzniks like millionaires lolling about in their swimming pools.\" He accuses the movement of not caring about the poor Mizrahi Jews who emigrated from Arab countries. \n\n\"But we helped to found this nation!\" shouts Hannah in disbelief.\n\nHow do you respond to this incitement? ", "answers": [{"answerBonusVariable": "rep", "answerIdeology": "Socialist", "rep": 5.0, "reply": "Your letter gets the attention of your fellow kibbutzniks, and the government, who reduces your farm subsidy. It hits your bottom line, but at least you stood up to the Premier.", "sol": 0.0, "pop": 0.0, "answerBonusValue": 5.0, "econ": -5.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Write a letter to the newspaper condeming Begin."}, {"answerBonusVariable": "rep", "answerIdeology": "Marxist", "rep": 0.0, "reply": "You join forces throughout your federation to take on the Likud in the next election. You fail, again, but your members are energized by the fight.", "sol": 5.0, "pop": 0.0, "answerBonusValue": 5.0, "econ": 0.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Organize a campaign to elect more left-wing MKs."}, {"answerBonusVariable": "pop", "answerIdeology": "Labor Zionist", "rep": -5.0, "reply": "Nobody complains about having a bigger pool. Your members leave politics to those people outside your fence. New members are drawn to the \"millionaire\" lifestyle.", "sol": 5.0, "pop": 10.0, "answerBonusValue": 1.25, "econ": -5.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Invest kibbutz money into improving the swimming pool."}], "type": "E", "hook": "\"We might have swimming pools, but we are hardly millionaires!\""}, {"text": "Your factory has grown and now exports its products overseas. \n\nManagers say it needs a proper board of directors to attract new capital for expansion. \"It's time for the kibbutz factory to operate like a real business,\" says Amos. \n\n\"But the factory is a creation of the community,\" argues Sarah, \"and should be run by and for all kibbutzniks, not just for profit.\" \n\nWhat do you advise? ", "answers": [{"answerBonusVariable": "rep", "answerIdeology": "Socialist", "rep": -5.0, "reply": "Members aren't happy to lose their say in the factory. But profits rise when a professional manager and a board of directors can make quick decisions. ", "sol": -5.0, "pop": 5.0, "answerBonusValue": -10.0, "econ": 1.5, "trig": "", "answer": "Yes. The factory should organize a board of directors."}, {"answerBonusVariable": "rep", "answerIdeology": "Socialist", "rep": 5.0, "reply": "You run every decision through the General Assembly. Meetings go late and the factory loses money, but you are proud it's still a collective enterprise.", "sol": 5.0, "pop": -5.0, "answerBonusValue": 10.0, "econ": 0.75, "trig": "", "answer": "No. Let members run the factory."}], "type": "E", "hook": "\"It's time for professional management!\""}, {"text": "A group of young kibbutzniks are disappointed with the loss of your community's pioneering philosophy and political activism. \n\n\"We've become a country suburb of pseudo-socialists!\" they lament. They plan to leave the kibbutz and start an anarchist commune in the Negev Desert devoted to free love and absolute equality. \n\n\"Head off to the desert!\" shouts Moishe. \"You will fail like every New Age commune!\"\n\nHow do you reply? ", "answers": [{"answerBonusVariable": "sol", "answerIdeology": "Marxist", "rep": 0.0, "reply": "The young idealists start an \"ecovillage\" in the desert. They succeed and their new kibbutz grows. Several other young members leave and join this new movement.", "sol": 5.0, "pop": 0.75, "answerBonusValue": -10.0, "econ": -5.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Tell them to leave and start their own commune."}, {"answerBonusVariable": "rep", "answerIdeology": "Socialist", "rep": 0.0, "reply": "You convince the dissatisfied young members to stay. Several take leadership roles. They ask for decisions by consensus not committee. It feels hippy-dippy to the founders, but your kibbutz evolves with the times.", "sol": -5.0, "pop": 5.0, "answerBonusValue": 5.0, "econ": 5.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Ask them to stay and help improve your kibbbutz."}], "type": "E", "hook": "\"Go live like Lawrence of Arabia!\""}, {"text": "Launched in 1982, the Lebanon War drags on. Reserve soldiers are sent to the front. A kibbutz-born tank commander is killed in combat. Several of your younger members refuse to serve in the Army rather than be sent to Lebanon or the Occupied Territories. \n\n\"Service is part of every Israeli citizen's duty!\" says Uri, a veteran of several wars.\n\n\"Not when it's for the wrong cause,\" argues Dudu, a young peacenik.\n\nWhat do you tell them? ", "answers": [{"answerBonusVariable": "rep", "answerIdeology": "Labor Zionist", "rep": 5.0, "reply": "The objectors agree to take up their Reserve duty. Several of the soldiers are killed in Lebanon on a routine patrol. Your kibbutz is hailed throughout the country for the sacrifice of your members, but at what cost?", "sol": -5.0, "pop": -5.0, "answerBonusValue": 10.0, "econ": 0.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Convince them to serve in the IDF."}, {"answerBonusVariable": "sol", "answerIdeology": "Religious", "rep": 5.0, "reply": "Your kibbutz rallies around the objectors. Right-wing politicians criticize your community as \"left-wing bleeding hearts,\" and locals refuse to buy your farm produce. Your young members serve time and return home to work in peace.", "sol": 5.0, "pop": 5.0, "answerBonusValue": -10.0, "econ": -5.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Pay their legal fees in support."}, {"answerBonusVariable": "sol", "answerIdeology": "Marxist", "rep": -5.0, "reply": "Your young members are shocked by the harsh punishment. Some family members leave too. ", "sol": 5.0, "pop": -5.0, "answerBonusValue": 0.75, "econ": 0.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Kick them out for not serving."}], "type": "E", "hook": "\"Army service is part of our duty!\""}, {"text": "Your kibbutz accepts its first group of young German volunteers. The new arrivals cause anxiety in several kibbutzniks who are Holocaust survivors. \n\n\"The sound of German brings tears to my eyes,\" says Menachem, who lost his family in Auschwitz. \"These volunteers remind me of the camp guards who marched my parents to the ovens.\" \n\nHow do you resolve their concerns? ", "answers": [{"answerBonusVariable": "rep", "answerIdeology": "Marxist", "rep": -5.0, "reply": "Your community gets a reputation as unwelcoming to visitors. But your old-timers feel at peace. Again", "sol": 5.0, "pop": 0.0, "answerBonusValue": -10.0, "econ": -5.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Insist that the German volunteers leave."}, {"answerBonusVariable": "sol", "answerIdeology": "Labor Zionist", "rep": 0.0, "reply": "The volunteers stay, but the old-timers aren't happy. They still hear German spoken in the dining room and feel betrayed. ", "sol": -5.0, "pop": 0.0, "answerBonusValue": -5.0, "econ": 5.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Allow the volunteers to stay. "}, {"answerBonusVariable": "rep", "answerIdeology": "Religious", "rep": 5.0, "reply": "Not everyone is happy with this compromise to let the German volunteers stay, but the conversations evolve into a program of reconciliation between young Germans and older Jews on your kibbutz.", "sol": -5.0, "pop": 0.0, "answerBonusValue": 10.0, "econ": 0.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Arrange meetings with the survivors to tell their stories to the volunteers."}], "type": "I", "hook": "\"Maybe they can talk about the Holocaust...\""}]}, {"newEra": {"sol": -10.0, "type": "newEra", "rep": 0.0, "text": "The financial crisis persists. Politics in Israel becomes a stalemate. A fatal truck accident in a refugee camp sparks the Palestinian people in the West Bank and Gaza to protest the Israeli Army's occupation. \n\nGeneral strikes, civil disobedience and boycotts of Israeli institutions lead to clashes with stones and Molotov cocktails. The IDF tries to suppress the protests, with little success but many casualties.\n\nWithin the borders of Israel, your kibbutz is struggling to stay afloat and remain meaningful...", "pop": 5.0, "hook": "1986-1995: From Uprising till Oslo", "econ": 0.8}, "questions": [{"text": "The kibbutz discovers a long-time member named Gilad has been stealing equipment from the factory and selling it on the black market. He has a wife and three kids on the kibbutz.\n\n\"This is a violation of our community!\" says Shmuel. \"He must leave!\"\n\n\"But what about the family?\" asks Dudu.\n\n How do you penalize his actions?", "answers": [{"answerBonusVariable": "sol", "answerIdeology": "Labor Zionist", "rep": 5.0, "reply": "Gilad thanks the kibbutz for their forgiveness. Many members think he has broken the trust of the community. And items start to go missing in other workplaces.", "sol": -5.0, "pop": 0.0, "answerBonusValue": -5.0, "econ": -5.0, "trig": "", "answer": "He must quit the factory but can work in another branch."}, {"answerBonusVariable": "rep", "answerIdeology": "Socialist", "rep": 5.0, "reply": "It's difficult to send off a member, but your community agrees to send a message. Gilad never returns to the grounds of the kibbutz. ", "sol": 0.0, "pop": -5.0, "answerBonusValue": 5.0, "econ": -5.0, "trig": "", "answer": "He and his family are banished."}, {"answerBonusVariable": "rep", "answerIdeology": "Religious", "rep": -5.0, "reply": "The police investigate and recover most of the stolen property. Gilad is sentenced to five years in prison and his family leaves the community in shame. Other kibbutzniks wonder why you couldn't have solved the issue internally.", "sol": 0.0, "pop": -5.0, "answerBonusValue": -10.0, "econ": 5.0, "trig": "", "answer": "You turn him over to authorities to be prosecuted."}], "type": "I", "hook": "\"Let the police settle the matter.\" "}, {"text": "Kibbutz-born children don't come back as members after their Army service. Instead they travel the world or move to Tel Aviv. Life is elsewhere.\n\n\"Who wants to be a farmer anymore?\" asks Rebecca, a third-generation daughter of the kibbutz.\n\nHow can your aging kibbutz rejuvenate its membership?", "answers": [{"answerBonusVariable": "rep", "answerIdeology": "Marxist", "rep": 0.0, "reply": "Your investment in new facilities encourages a wave of returns from children of the kibbutz. The community feels lively again. ", "sol": 5.0, "pop": 1.25, "answerBonusValue": -10.0, "econ": -5.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Offer returning children the newest apartments and build a kibbutz disco."}, {"answerBonusVariable": "rep", "answerIdeology": "Socialist", "rep": 5.0, "reply": "More young members leave. The community feels adrift. But your reputation for holding to the ideals of the communal philosophy is renowned.", "sol": 0.75, "pop": 0.75, "answerBonusValue": 10.0, "econ": 0.75, "trig": "", "answer": "Do nothing. Your children will return when they tire of city life. "}, {"answerBonusVariable": "rep", "answerIdeology": "Labor Zionist", "rep": 5.0, "reply": "You attract new groups of pioneers from youth groups in England the U.S. They are good workers but sometines anoy longtime kibbutzniks.", "sol": 5.0, "pop": 5.0, "answerBonusValue": -10.0, "econ": 5.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Recruit from the youth movement and from Diaspora Jews with a passion for Zionism."}], "type": "E", "hook": "\"What do young people want these days?\""}, {"text": "The managers of your factory want to expand by spinning off the operation from the kibbutz and going public on an American stock exchange. \n\n\"But then the factory will no longer belong to us,\" warns Moishe, one of your founders.\n\nWhat do you advise?", "answers": [{"answerBonusVariable": "sol", "answerIdeology": "Marxist", "rep": -5.0, "reply": "Your investment pays off and you expand your factory. Other kibbutzes think you've gone capitalist, but who cares? You are able to raise the monthly allowance for members due to the new profits.", "sol": 5.0, "pop": 10.0, "answerBonusValue": 0.75, "econ": 20.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Let the factory go public."}, {"answerBonusVariable": "sol", "answerIdeology": "Religious", "rep": 0.0, "reply": "It takes a long time to negotiate a loan from the federation and it's only enough to renovate half the factory. Meanwhile, competitors expand and cut into your profits.", "sol": 0.0, "pop": 0.0, "answerBonusValue": 0.75, "econ": -10.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Try to borrow money from the kibbutz federation instead."}, {"answerBonusVariable": "sol", "answerIdeology": "Labor Zionist", "rep": 5.0, "reply": "You leave playing the markets for the financiers in Tel Aviv. You stick to earning a living with your hands. But it's hard to compete against imports from Africa and Asia.", "sol": 0.0, "pop": 0.0, "answerBonusValue": 0.75, "econ": -5.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Don't risk an IPO."}], "type": "E", "hook": "\"An IPO will make us millions!\""}, {"text": "A  group of foreign volunteers make noise at night, show up late or hungover to work, and break farm equipment \"by accident\". They are popular with younger kibbutzniks for the parties they throw.\n\n\"They are ruining our own children!\" warns Shmuel.\n\n\"Really?\" says Yosef. \"Who cares, as long as they do their jobs.\"\n\nHow do you resolve the conflict?", "answers": [{"answerBonusVariable": "rep", "answerIdeology": "Labor Zionist", "rep": -10.0, "reply": "Your members appreciate your hardline approach even if it's tough to make up for the lost labour. Volunteers no longer spread word about your kibbutz, hwoever.", "sol": 0.0, "pop": -5.0, "answerBonusValue": -10.0, "econ": -5.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Close down the volunteer program."}, {"answerBonusVariable": "rep", "answerIdeology": "Religious", "rep": 0.0, "reply": "The Volunteer Quarter settles down when you send away the ring leaders of the all-night parties. The remaining volunteers put in a full day in the fields.", "sol": 0.0, "pop": 0.0, "answerBonusValue": 5.0, "econ": 0.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Expel the worst offenders."}, {"answerBonusVariable": "sol", "answerIdeology": "Religious", "rep": -5.0, "reply": "Older members think you are soft on the noisy intruders. Younger members like to hang out and drink with the foreign workers. One stays and marries into the kibbutz", "sol": -5.0, "pop": 5.0, "answerBonusValue": -10.0, "econ": 5.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Ignore the disturbance. Volunteers will be volunteers."}], "type": "I", "hook": "\"Throw them all off the kibbutz!\""}, {"text": "You are one of the last kibbutzes to maintain a children's house for communal child-rearing. Several members demand that their kids be allowed to stay in their rooms.\n\n\"Raising our children together inspires the spirit of communal living!\" says Sarah and Tonya, who run the children's house.\n\nWhat do you recommend?", "answers": [{"answerBonusVariable": "rep", "answerIdeology": "Socialist", "rep": -10.0, "reply": "It feels like the end of an era, but parents welcome the chance to have their children sleep in their own rooms. A few former members return to the kibbutz ", "sol": 5.0, "pop": 10.0, "answerBonusValue": 0.75, "econ": 5.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Yes. Let children sleep at home. "}, {"answerBonusVariable": "sol", "answerIdeology": "Labor Zionist", "rep": 1.5, "reply": "It's not a popular decision to keep running the children's houses. Several families leave. You become known as one of the last \"pure\" kibbutzes.", "sol": -10.0, "pop": -10.0, "answerBonusValue": -10.0, "econ": 0.0, "trig": "", "answer": "No. Keep communal child-rearing. "}], "type": "I", "hook": "\"Enough with ideology! Children need their parents!\""}, {"text": "The PLO calls a three-day strike  to support the Intifada in the West Bank and Gaza. Arab workers in your fields and factory refuse to come to work in solidarity with this strike. Their actions will cost the kibbutz money. \n\n\"Let them go,\" says Gideon. \"We can find true Israelis to work for us.\"\n\nHow do you react? ", "answers": [{"answerBonusVariable": "sol", "answerIdeology": "Marxist", "rep": -5.0, "reply": "It's a tough decision but good for the bottom line. The loss of the Arab workers disconnects your community from the local Palestinian communities and their struggles. ", "sol": 0.0, "pop": 10.0, "answerBonusValue": -10.0, "econ": 10.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Hire new employees or replace them with volunteers."}, {"answerBonusVariable": "rep", "answerIdeology": "Labor Zionist", "rep": 5.0, "reply": "Not everyone agrees to take a loss until the workers return, but they thank you for your understanding. ", "sol": -5.0, "pop": 0.0, "answerBonusValue": -10.0, "econ": -5.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Let the Arab labourers return after the strike."}], "type": "E", "hook": "\"If they don't want to work, fire them!\""}, {"text": "The hyper-inflation and sky-rocketing interest rates has through Israel's economy into turmoil. Kibbutzes' debts balloon. The kibbutz federation negotiates with the government to get a bail-out from the banks. \n\n\"We are strongest as a united movement!\" argues Moishe.\n\nWhat do you recommend? ", "answers": [{"answerBonusVariable": "sol", "answerIdeology": "Socialist", "rep": 5.0, "reply": "The negotiations with the government plod on for years. Eventually, they reach a agreement to reduce the debts for all kibbutzes, a costly deal that still leaves you without much money.", "sol": 0.0, "pop": -5.0, "answerBonusValue": 5.0, "econ": -10.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Join the negotiations and accept the Kibbutz Agreement deal."}, {"answerBonusVariable": "econ", "answerIdeology": "Labor Zionist", "rep": -5.0, "reply": "You go your own way and escape your debts faster than other kibbutzes. Other kibbutzes accuse you of leaving them to sink rather than helping out. ", "sol": 5.0, "pop": 0.0, "answerBonusValue": 5.0, "econ": 5.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Try to negotiate a deal on our own terms."}], "type": "E", "hook": "\"We can negotiate a better deal for our debts!\""}, {"text": "The economic crisis forces your financial committee to consider more drastic actions and cutbacks. \n\n\"We must be ruthless,\" says Reuven, your young economic director, \"or the kibbtuz will fail!\"\n\nWhere do you begin to reduce the budget? ", "answers": [{"answerBonusVariable": "sol", "answerIdeology": "Marxist", "rep": -5.0, "reply": "The drastic cuts are a shock to the spirits of your members. Several families leave. But it helps to balance your books.", "sol": 0.0, "pop": 0.75, "answerBonusValue": -5.0, "econ": 1.25, "trig": "", "answer": "Education and childcare."}, {"answerBonusVariable": "sol", "answerIdeology": "Socialist", "rep": 0.0, "reply": "Members aren't happy about losing free meals. But it helps to reduce the economic bleeding.", "sol": 0.75, "pop": -5.0, "answerBonusValue": -5.0, "econ": 10.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Free meals in the dining hall and extra programs in the social centre."}, {"answerBonusVariable": "sol", "answerIdeology": "Religious", "rep": 0.8, "reply": "Your founders feel they are being abandoned all for the sake of a few shekels.", "sol": -5.0, "pop": -5.0, "answerBonusValue": -5.0, "econ": 1.25, "trig": "", "answer": "Healthcare and the seniors center."}, {"answerBonusVariable": "rep", "answerIdeology": "Labor Zionist", "rep": 0.0, "reply": "Cutbacks to your industrial branches reduce complaints. But the financial results for the next quarter are grim. ", "sol": 5.0, "pop": 0.0, "answerBonusValue": -10.0, "econ": 0.75, "trig": "", "answer": "No new investments in farm equipment or the factory."}], "type": "B", "hook": "\"We must slash our biggest costs...\""}]}, {"newEra": {"sol": 0.8, "type": "newEra", "rep": 0.0, "text": "The Oslo Peace Accords bring a hope for peace. But then comes more sadness. On November 5, 1995, after a speech in Tel Aviv to a crowd of 100,000, Prime Minister Yitzhak Rabin is shot and killed by a Jewish fanatic. Unrest grows in the Palestinian Territories. Security becomes more important than peace for the new right-wing government in Israel\n\nYour communities feel like islands of socialism amid a stormy sea of capitalist competition...", "pop": -5.0, "hook": "1996-2005: Start-Up Nation", "econ": 0.8}, "questions": [{"text": "To save money, your financial manager recommends that the kibbutz hire a contractor to run the kitchen \"We will charge members for lunch,\" says Reuven, \"and only open the dining hall for Shabbat dinners. \n\nMany members like three free meals a day. \"Only people who break bread will stay united!\" says Ziva.\n\nWhat do you decide?", "answers": [{"answerBonusVariable": "sol", "answerIdeology": "Socialist", "rep": 0.0, "reply": "You save money by contracting out the kitchen duties. But members stop coming as often. Neighbours retreat and eat with their families rather than with the kibbutz.", "sol": -5.0, "pop": 0.0, "answerBonusValue": -5.0, "econ": 10.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Close for lunch and charge a fee for lunch and dinners."}, {"answerBonusVariable": "econ", "answerIdeology": "Religious", "rep": 5.0, "reply": "It's a costly expense, but the dining hall remains the hub of social and political life on the kibbutz. ", "sol": 5.0, "pop": 0.0, "answerBonusValue": -10.0, "econ": 0.75, "trig": "", "answer": "Maintain a full, free kitchen for all three meals."}, {"answerBonusVariable": "rep", "answerIdeology": "Socialist", "rep": -5.0, "reply": "It cuts a big expense from your bottom line. But the empty dining hall reminds members of all that they've lost. Several families leave.", "sol": -10.0, "pop": -5.0, "answerBonusValue": 0.75, "econ": 1.25, "trig": "", "answer": "Shut down the kitchen entirely"}], "type": "I", "hook": "\"Do we need to eat together to stay united?\""}, {"text": "Several new members are Orthodox. They want the kibbutz to add a synagogue and the kitchen to only serve kosher food. \n\n\"We must change to meet the faith of our nation,\" says Yosef, a longtime kibbutznik who found religion. \n\n\"Ugh!\" shouts Moishe, an ardent Marxist. \"Religion is the opiate of the masses!\"\n\nThe General Assembly must reach a decision. ", "answers": [{"answerBonusVariable": "sol", "answerIdeology": "Marxist", "rep": 0.0, "reply": "It costs money to add the synagogue and upgrade the kitchen, although it's not as much of a hassle to accommodate the religious newcomers. More observant members join the kibbutz.", "sol": -5.0, "pop": 10.0, "answerBonusValue": 0.75, "econ": -10.0, "trig": "NOT if R ", "answer": "Build a synagogue and keep a kosher kitchen. "}, {"answerBonusVariable": "rep", "answerIdeology": "Labor Zionist", "rep": 5.0, "reply": "The synagogue becomes a hub of communal activity on the kibbutz. ", "sol": 0.0, "pop": 0.0, "answerBonusValue": 10.0, "econ": -5.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Build a synagogue but let people keep kosher on their own."}, {"answerBonusVariable": "rep", "answerIdeology": "Religious", "rep": 10.0, "reply": "The religious members make an exodus from your kibbutz. Your members remain united in staying secular, even as the rest of Israel grows more religious.", "sol": 5.0, "pop": 0.75, "answerBonusValue": 0.5, "econ": 0.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Tell them to join a religious kibbutz."}], "type": "I", "hook": "\"Why don't they move to a religious kibbutz?\""}, {"text": "Your kibbutz members no longer want to do field work, while international volunteers are too unreliable and transient. \n\n\"We need to shut down the volunteer program,\" says Amos, \"and hire guest workers from Thailand. Every kibbutz is doing it.\" \n\n\"Whatever happened to our motto?\" asks Sarah. \"Neither exploited nor exploiter.\" \n\nWhat do you recommend? ", "answers": [{"answerBonusVariable": "rep", "answerIdeology": "Marxist", "rep": -10.0, "reply": "The motion to hire Thai guest workers passes after a vigorous debate. The guest workers are hard-working, but they form a community of second-class citizens in your utopia of equals.", "sol": -10.0, "pop": 10.0, "answerBonusValue": -10.0, "econ": 1.5, "trig": "", "answer": "Hire Thai guest workers for the field jobs."}, {"answerBonusVariable": "rep", "answerIdeology": "Socialist", "rep": 5.0, "reply": "The idea to hire guest workers is voted down after a heated debate. Volunteers are less reliable and kibbutzniks shirk off the real fieldwork. The agricultural output suffers, but you can look at everyone in your dining hall and know they are equals.", "sol": 0.0, "pop": 5.0, "answerBonusValue": 10.0, "econ": -10.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Use kibbutzniks and volunteers for agricultural work."}, {"answerBonusVariable": "sol", "answerIdeology": "Socialist", "rep": 0.75, "reply": "Taming the land was at the heart of your kibbutz for decades. It shocks the founders when you lease out the fields and focus on your factories. But that's where the profit margins are.", "sol": -5.0, "pop": 0.0, "answerBonusValue": -10.0, "econ": 1.5, "trig": "", "answer": "Shut down the agricultural operations and focus on the factory."}], "type": "E", "hook": "\"Thai workers could do it for cheaper!\""}, {"text": "Younger kibbutzniks say  the kibbutz has lost its vision and should join the international movement of \"eco-villages\" by investing more resources in educational  programs and alternative energy projects. \n\n\"Eco-Zionism is the way of the future!\" says Dudu, who tends the gardens.\n\n\"Enough with these naive hippy schesm!\" says Amos, your factory manager.\n\nHow do you resolve their conflict? ", "answers": [{"answerBonusVariable": "econ", "answerIdeology": "Labor Zionist", "rep": 10.0, "reply": "The new \"eco-center\" on the kibbutz draws volunteers from around the world and becomes a hub for environmentalism in Victoria. Your community becomes known as a \"Israel's greenest kibbutz\"--and your members discover a new cause to rally around.", "sol": 5.0, "pop": 10.0, "answerBonusValue": 0.75, "econ": 0.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Become an eco-kibbutz."}, {"answerBonusVariable": "pop", "answerIdeology": "Socialist", "rep": 0.0, "reply": "You double-down on expanding your factory and the recycling efforts fall by the wayside. A few of the younger environmentalists leave to start an eco-commune. You will leave others to save the planet. You need to survive as a kibbutz first.", "sol": -5.0, "pop": -5.0, "answerBonusValue": 0.75, "econ": 1.5, "trig": "", "answer": "Focus on creating jobs rather than environmental causes."}], "type": "E", "hook": "\"Let the hippies tend their gardens!\""}, {"text": "The kibbutz feels adrift. Yes, you have your farm fields and your factories and living expenses paid for by the collective. But something feels missing. You field several proposals for a new project that could be added to the kibbutz that might re-energize its original mission of social good. \n\n\"We must pursue tikkun olam,\" says Rebecca, a young activist, \"and learn to heal the world again.\"\n\nWhat do you recommend?", "answers": [{"answerBonusVariable": "rep", "answerIdeology": "Religious", "rep": 5.0, "reply": "It's an expensive investment to reconfigure your entire kibbutz into a \"home for life\" that accommodates these new residents. But your kibbutz gains a reputation as Israel's leading centre for adults with disabilities under the kibbutz philosophy of mutual aid.", "sol": 0.0, "pop": 1.5, "answerBonusValue": 10.0, "econ": -10.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Open a home for adults with physical and mental disabilities."}, {"answerBonusVariable": "sol", "answerIdeology": "Socialist", "rep": 10.0, "reply": "The Kibbutz Dance Company is a success. The government funds international tours around the world. New members come to your community to work as set designers and dance assistants.", "sol": 0.0, "pop": 10.0, "answerBonusValue": -5.0, "econ": 10.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Let a choreographer start a Dance Village and training center."}, {"answerBonusVariable": "sol", "answerIdeology": "Marxist", "rep": 0.0, "reply": "The orchid garden entices tourists. Most of your members don't pay much attention but appreciate the extra revenue.", "sol": 0.0, "pop": 0.0, "answerBonusValue": -10.0, "econ": 1.5, "trig": "", "answer": "Create a botanical attraction with rare orchids and a paid admission."}, {"answerBonusVariable": "rep", "answerIdeology": "Labor Zionist", "rep": 10.0, "reply": "Your members come together to record and preserve the stories of the survivors. It's a break-even project, but your kibbutz becomes known as having the most extensive Holocaust museum in Israel outside of Yad Vashem.", "sol": 5.0, "pop": 0.0, "answerBonusValue": 10.0, "econ": -5.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Build a museum about the Holocaust and its aftermath."}], "type": "E", "hook": "\"We need a new direction!\""}, {"text": "After a terrible helicopter accident kills more than 70 soldiers on the border of Lebanon, a group of women from your kibbutz begin a public protest to demand that the government bring home its soldiers. The protest grows bigger. The activists march on the Prime Minister's office. \n\n\"Women shouldn't interfere in military affairs,\" warns Gideon, an IDF officer. \n\n\"It's time the generals listened to the mothers of this nation!\" says Tonya.\n\n What do you advise? ", "answers": [{"answerBonusVariable": "sol", "answerIdeology": "Religious", "rep": -10.0, "reply": "The leaders of the movement are disappointed with the lack of support. One family leaves. Their protest eventually convinces the Army to leave Lebanon, but your community can take little credit for this change.", "sol": -5.0, "pop": -5.0, "answerBonusValue": 10.0, "econ": 0.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Make clear the women are speaking as mothers and not as kibbutzniks. "}, {"answerBonusVariable": "rep", "answerIdeology": "Marxist", "rep": 5.0, "reply": "Your kibbutz gets attacked by right-wing pundits as gutless peaceniks. But your support for the protesters helps to rally support. Eventually, the majority of citizens press the government until the Army leaves Lebanon. ", "sol": 5.0, "pop": 0.0, "answerBonusValue": 20.0, "econ": -10.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Provide the protesters with resources and encouragement."}], "type": "I", "hook": "\"Do we need to agree on every issue?\""}, {"text": "Amos, your business manager, suggests a couple of options for your kibbutz to industrialize and become a player in Start-Up Nation. Not everyone agrees, though.\n\n\"Leave capitalism to the suits in Tel Aviv,\" says Dudu. \"We are here to work the land.\"\n\nWhich do you prefer?", "answers": [{"answerBonusVariable": "rep", "answerIdeology": "Religious", "rep": 10.0, "reply": "Your kibbutz plays it safe and sticks to its old factory and farming operations. But it becomes harder to stay competitive and your work branches go into debt.", "sol": 0.0, "pop": -5.0, "answerBonusValue": 10.0, "econ": -20.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Stick to farming."}, {"answerBonusVariable": "rep", "answerIdeology": "Labor Zionist", "rep": 5.0, "reply": "Your innovative irrigation system makes the deserts bloom and is sold around the world. New members arrive to run the expanding factory and sales operations.", "sol": 0.0, "pop": 1.25, "answerBonusValue": 10.0, "econ": 10.0, "trig": "", "answer": "A factory to produce drip-irrigation systems."}, {"answerBonusVariable": "rep", "answerIdeology": "Marxist", "rep": 5.0, "reply": "Not everyone is thrilled that your kibbutz has become a military supplier. But with the Iraq War, your factory finds a profitable customer in the U.S. Army.  ", "sol": -5.0, "pop": 10.0, "answerBonusValue": 0.75, "econ": 1.5, "trig": "", "answer": "A factory to produce armor for military vehicles."}, {"answerBonusVariable": "sol", "answerIdeology": "Socialist", "rep": 0.0, "reply": "You manage to compete against Nikon and Zeiss. The factory also supplies work opportunities for old and new members.", "sol": 5.0, "pop": 5.0, "answerBonusValue": 5.0, "econ": 1.25, "trig": "", "answer": "A factory to design progressive lenses."}], "type": "E", "hook": "\"High-tech is the way of the future!\""}, {"text": "Kibbutz Masada, a community in your movement, votes to \"privatize and will no longer pay members an equal amount no matter their job. This decision causes a controversy. Your movement asks kibbutz leaders for your opinions. \n\n\"Kick them out!\" urges Shmuel one of your founders.\n\nWhat do you think? ", "answers": [{"answerBonusVariable": "rep", "answerIdeology": "Marxist", "rep": 5.0, "reply": "After your hardline stance, Masada leaves your federation and no longer pays into the collective fund. ", "sol": -5.0, "pop": 0.0, "answerBonusValue": 10.0, "econ": -10.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Masada should be forced out of the movement and lose all privileges, including calling itself a kibbutz."}, {"answerBonusVariable": "rep", "answerIdeology": "Religious", "rep": 0.0, "reply": "Your generosity is returned when the privatized kibbutz lends you some economic consultants. Maybe one day you will consider following their path?", "sol": 5.0, "pop": 0.0, "answerBonusValue": 10.0, "econ": 0.0, "trig": "", "answer": "As long as Masada look after its neediest members, it's still a kibbutz."}, {"answerBonusVariable": "sol", "answerIdeology": "Marxist", "rep": -5.0, "reply": "It's obvious that the movement needs to evolve, but you spark a controversy by raising the possibility of privatization.", "sol": -5.0, "pop": 0.0, "answerBonusValue": -10.0, "econ": 5.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Masada made the right decision and the whole movement should consider privatization."}], "type": "E", "hook": "\"Their kibbutz is no longer a kibbutz!\""}, {"text": "An economic consultant from Tel Aviv offers his services to add economic efficiencies. \"I've successfully helped other kibbutzes recalibrate from socialism to capitalism while keeping the community happy,\" he says. \n\n\"Yes,\" says Amos, a factory manager. \"The kibbutz's finances are too complex to handle on our own.\"\n\nDo you hire him?", "answers": [{"answerBonusVariable": "econ", "answerIdeology": "Labor Zionist", "rep": -5.0, "reply": "Not everyone likes turning over the keys to your economic engine to a non-member. But the consultant cuts expenses and retools your operations to be more efficient. Profits rise, even if it means members are forced into jobs they don't always like.", "sol": -5.0, "pop": 0.0, "answerBonusValue": 1.25, "econ": 10.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Yes. You hire the consultant."}, {"answerBonusVariable": "sol", "answerIdeology": "Labor Zionist", "rep": 5.0, "reply": "It feels good to maintain your freedom. But your business operations continue to stumble. Every decision is mired in long debates. You are admired for your independence. But your debts only grow_ and members leave to find more more comfortable lives in the city.", "sol": 5.0, "pop": -5.0, "answerBonusValue": -15.0, "econ": -10.0, "trig": "", "answer": "No. You tell him he's a vulture preying on kibbutzes."}], "type": "E", "hook": "\"Our kibbutz economy has become too complex for amateurs!\""}]}, {"newEra": {"sol": 0.0, "type": "newEra", "rep": 0.0, "text": "The kibbutz movement prepares to celebrate its 100th anniversary in 2010. It has much to celebrate but many regrets, too. The number of international volunteers has dwindled. Many members have left. The role of the kibbutz in Israeli society has diminished. \n\nYour founders' utopian vision seems out-of-date in a multicultural nation led by high-tech entrepreneurs, nationalistic politicians and religious settlers. \n\nWhat role does the kibbutz have in the 21st century? ", "pop": -10.0, "hook": "2005 - present: The End of Utopia?", "econ": 0.0}, "questions": [{"text": "The government is building a security fence to divide the West Bank from Israel to stop Palestinian infiltrators. The fence will cut across a corner of kibbutz property. You will lose access to a small field and your Arab neighbours will be separated from a larger olive orchard on the Israeli side of the Wall. \n\n\"We can't afford this loss of land,\" says Haim, the agricultural manager.\n\n\"What we can't afford is this violation of international law!\" says Rebecca, a community activist.\n\nHow do you react? ", "answers": [{"answerBonusVariable": "rep", "answerIdeology": "Marxist", "rep": 0.0, "reply": "Your swap fields for the old orchards and maintain friendly relations with your Palestinian neighbours, even separated by the barrier.", "sol": 5.0, "pop": 0.0, "answerBonusValue": 0.5, "econ": 5.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Accept the Security Fence and convince the Arab villagers to swap your field for their orchards. "}, {"answerBonusVariable": "econ", "answerIdeology": "Labor Zionist", "rep": -5.0, "reply": "The government offers funding to cover your losses and more. You feel bought off, but it's better than no compensation. ", "sol": -5.0, "pop": 0.0, "answerBonusValue": 1.25, "econ": 10.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Lobby the government for lost income from the fields."}, {"answerBonusVariable": "rep", "answerIdeology": "Marxist", "rep": 5.0, "reply": "Your kibbutz becomes a hub for Israeli protests against the Wall. Some neighbours refuse to shop at your kibbutz store because they feel you are \"Arab lovers\". But you fight for a united Israel.", "sol": 0.0, "pop": 0.0, "answerBonusValue": 1.5, "econ": -10.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Unite with your Palestinian neighbours to protest the Wall. "}], "type": "E", "hook": "\"This is a violation of our lands!\""}, {"text": "Gonan, a young member, was serving in the Army near Gaza when he was captured by Hamas militants. He has been held hostage for nearly a year. Hamas wants Israel to release 1,000 Palestinian prisoners in exchange. \n\n\"You must pressure the government!\" says Menachem, Gonan's father. \n\n\"No life is worth a thousand terrorists free again,\" says Gideon, an IDF officer.\n\nWhat do you do? ", "answers": [{"answerBonusVariable": "sol", "answerIdeology": "Religious", "rep": -5.0, "reply": "\"How can you abandon our son?\" the family laments andy leaves the kibbutz for the city. It takes years before the government  negotiates the release of Gonan. The trauma of his captivity haunts your kibbutz.", "sol": -5.0, "pop": -5.0, "answerBonusValue": -10.0, "econ": 0.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Let the government handle negotiations."}, {"answerBonusVariable": "rep", "answerIdeology": "Marxist", "rep": 5.0, "reply": "Your kibbutz rallies behind efforts to get a deal. Right-wing pundits complain you are endangering the country's security. Gonan 's family celebrates his return in the dining room.", "sol": 0.0, "pop": 2.0, "answerBonusValue": 10.0, "econ": -10.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Organize a march on the P.M.'s residence and to demand a deal with Hamas."}], "type": "I", "hook": "\"Can we leave our boy caged like an animal in Gaza?\""}, {"text": "Your Financial Manager calculates that the kibbutz could save money if you closed the on-site old-age home. \"They can stay in a much nicer facility in town,\" says Reuven.\n\n\"Why don't you put us on ice floes and send us away?\" scoffs Moishe.\n\nWhat do you recommend? ", "answers": [{"answerBonusVariable": "sol", "answerIdeology": "Socialist", "rep": 0.0, "reply": "It saves money to move the retirees to a better home in the city. But there is a loss in the spirit of the kibbutz. Weren't you supposed to watch out for everyone, young and old?", "sol": -10.0, "pop": -5.0, "answerBonusValue": -5.0, "econ": 10.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Yes. Use the money you save to invest back in the kibbutz."}, {"answerBonusVariable": "rep", "answerIdeology": "Socialist", "rep": 5.0, "reply": "Like welfare states in the West, it becomes expensive to provide for the needs of your retired members. But you honour their sacrifices with ones of your own.", "sol": 0.0, "pop": 0.0, "answerBonusValue": 10.0, "econ": -10.0, "trig": "", "answer": "No. Make cuts elsewhere on the kibbutz."}], "type": "I", "hook": "\"Have you no respect for the founders?\""}, {"text": "A consultant says that your kibbutz needs to cut costs. He recommends you lay off 90% of the laundry staff, stop subsidizing birth control and sell the school's musical instruments.\n\n\"I've looked at the numbers, and he's right,\" says Reuven, your financial manager.\n\n\"But art is more important than profits!\" pleads Yuval, a school teacher. \n\nShould you follow his advice?", "answers": [{"answerBonusVariable": "sol", "answerIdeology": "Socialist", "rep": -10.0, "reply": "The tough cuts stave off some of your debt. But the members are dispirited by the lost jobs and empty music room. Several leave.", "sol": -10.0, "pop": -5.0, "answerBonusValue": -5.0, "econ": 10.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Implement the consultant's plans."}, {"answerBonusVariable": "rep", "answerIdeology": "Socialist", "rep": 5.0, "reply": "\"Don't say I didn't warn you,\" says the consultant. Your financial future doesn't look good.", "sol": 0.0, "pop": 0.0, "answerBonusValue": 10.0, "econ": 0.75, "trig": "", "answer": "Fire the consultant and ignore his plan."}, {"answerBonusVariable": "rep", "answerIdeology": "Marxist", "rep": 0.0, "reply": "It's a decent compromise. But you still wonder Is it too little too late? The consultant insists you will need to make bigger cuts sooner rather thn later.", "sol": -5.0, "pop": 0.0, "answerBonusValue": -10.0, "econ": -10.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Cut the laundry staff in half, offer five free condoms a month and retain enough instruments for a small school band. "}], "type": "E", "hook": "\"A kibbutz that sells its instruments sells its soul!\""}, {"text": "Your population is aging and your kibbutz sits on valuable country real estate. City-dwellers in Israel's hectic urban centers want to move to the rural suburbs. A developer offers to build a new subdivision and divide the profits with the kibbutz. \n\n\"This is a good opportunity to bring in steady revenue,\" says Reuven, your financial manager.\n\nWhat do you recommend?", "answers": [{"answerBonusVariable": "rep", "answerIdeology": "Religious", "rep": 0.0, "reply": "You decide to maintain traditional membership without letting in outsiders. Several kibbtuzniks decide to leave, if the community is unwilling to grow. The average age on your kibbutz gets higher every year.", "sol": -5.0, "pop": -10.0, "answerBonusValue": 10.0, "econ": -10.0, "trig": "", "answer": "You reject the subdivision."}, {"answerBonusVariable": "rep", "answerIdeology": "Marxist", "rep": -10.0, "reply": "You use a law to select residents who will contribute to the greater community. Critics accuse you of being racists.", "sol": 5.0, "pop": 10.0, "answerBonusValue": -10.0, "econ": 5.0, "trig": "", "answer": "You agree to the development only if you can interview prospective buyers and take families who will fit within your community."}, {"answerBonusVariable": "rep", "answerIdeology": "Socialist", "rep": -5.0, "reply": "Your advertising brings in more buyers than you can accommodate. Soon you have a waiting list. The new residents don't always get along with the older founders on your kibbutz, but their downpayments and rent pay off many of your debts. The sound of children playing filling the common grounds once more.", "sol": -5.0, "pop": 1.5, "answerBonusValue": -10.0, "econ": 1.5, "trig": "", "answer": "You embrace the project and market the subdivision throughout Israel."}, {"answerBonusVariable": "sol", "answerIdeology": "Labor Zionist", "rep": 1.5, "reply": "Not everyone agrees a co-existence community can work. And the financial manager laments the lost revenues from Jewish buyers. Secular Palestinian families line up to buy a home on your kibbutz,  which becomes a beacon of hope amin Israel.", "sol": -10.0, "pop": 10.0, "answerBonusValue": -10.0, "econ": 5.0, "trig": "", "answer": "You agree to the project, only if the buyers form a \"co-existence community\" of Jewish and Palestinian residents."}], "type": "E", "hook": "\"We can survive without becoming real-estate tycoons!\" "}, {"text": "Rocket fire from Lebanon or Gaza drives your members into bomb shelters. Many flee to safer regions of the country. Israel returns to a state of war. Your kibbutz economy suffers. The once-peaceable mood of your kibbutz is souring. \n\n\"We must fight back!\" says Gideon. \"An eye for an eye!\"\n\n\"What about the children?\" says Tonya, the head nanny.\n\nHow do to calm fears? ", "answers": [{"answerBonusVariable": "rep", "answerIdeology": "Marxist", "rep": -5.0, "reply": "The Army responds with air strikes and artillery barrages. Militants and civilians are killed. Life returns to what passes for \"normal\" on a border kibbutz. ", "sol": 0.0, "pop": 10.0, "answerBonusValue": -10.0, "econ": 10.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Demand a strong military response to stop the rockets."}, {"answerBonusVariable": "rep", "answerIdeology": "Labor Zionist", "rep": 5.0, "reply": "Living under the shower of rockets takes its toll on your members. Several families leave. But your kibbutz becomes a symbol of national resilience. ", "sol": -10.0, "pop": -10.0, "answerBonusValue": 1.5, "econ": -5.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Stay in the shelters and hope for a quick end to the conflict."}, {"answerBonusVariable": "rep", "answerIdeology": "Socialist", "rep": 10.0, "reply": "Right-wing politicians accuse your members of being weak-willed peaceniks. But your protest gets international attention.", "sol": 5.0, "pop": -5.0, "answerBonusValue": 10.0, "econ": -10.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Protest the retaliations and civilian deaths on both sides."}], "type": "E", "hook": "\"This is no way for people to live!\""}, {"text": "In 2005 Prime Minister Ariel Sharon surprises the country by ordering a unilateral withdrawal of Israeli settlements from Gaza. Many settlers must be forcibly removed by the Israeli Army. One settlement used to be a kibbutz. \n\n\"This is a a crime against Jewish patriots!\" complains GIdeon.\n\n\"Hardly,\" replies Dudu. \"They had no business on Palestinian land!\"\n\nHow do you react? ", "answers": [{"answerBonusVariable": "sol", "answerIdeology": "Labor Zionist", "rep": 10.0, "reply": "You lobby for further evacuations of settlements in the West Bank. That stance pushes you further out of the mainstream of Israeli public opinion.", "sol": 0.0, "pop": 0.0, "answerBonusValue": 0.5, "econ": -10.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Encourage the government to remove settlers from the West Bank, too."}, {"answerBonusVariable": "sol", "answerIdeology": "Marxist", "rep": -10.0, "reply": "You let the government know you think the settlers have been treated badly. Fellow kibbutzniks wonder if you have become right-wingers.", "sol": 0.0, "pop": 0.0, "answerBonusValue": -10.0, "econ": 0.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Condemn the eviction of fellow pioneers."}, {"answerBonusVariable": "rep", "answerIdeology": "Religious", "rep": 10.0, "reply": "It's difficult at first to integrate the settlers into your community, but they welcome a chance to contribute to your rural kibbutz rather than be relocated to a city.", "sol": -5.0, "pop": 20.0, "answerBonusValue": 1.5, "econ": 1.25, "trig": "", "answer": "Invite the settlers to live on your kibbutz."}], "type": "E", "hook": "\"Settlers are almost as bad as terrorists!\""}, {"text": "The kibbutz faces an existential crisis. Nobody believes that everyone is equal. Nobody believes your small village can change the world. Even the word \"kibbutz\" has no real meaning anymore. Most other kibbutzes have embraced Shinui or \"The Change\". \n\n\"Our children won't return if we don't offer them freedom,\" says Amos.\n\n\"No!\" shouts Hannah. \"Nothing in Israel is more original or valuable than the kibbutz! People can leave if they don't like it.\"\n\nThere has never been such an angry debate. What do you tell the General Assembly?", "answers": [{"answerBonusVariable": "rep", "answerIdeology": "Marxist", "rep": 0.5, "reply": "It's the end of your community as a kibbutz of equals. You rename it Friendly Gardens Village and let anyone move in or out as they please. You lease the farm lands to outsiders and sell off the factory off.\n\nIt's hard to believe you were once pioneers. But your former kibbutz offers a picturesque escape city life in Israel. You will leave saving the nation to the next generation....", "sol": 0.75, "pop": 1.5, "answerBonusValue": -10.0, "econ": 1.5, "trig": "", "answer": "Privatize the kibbutz."}, {"answerBonusVariable": "sol", "answerIdeology": "Socialist", "rep": -10.0, "reply": "It's a disappointment to give up the name \"kibbutz\". But the cooperative  moshav movement is nearly as old and played a vital role in settling Israel. Cooperation was the core of your philosophy, and your home still holds to that ideal.", "sol": 0.0, "pop": 5.0, "answerBonusValue": -10.0, "econ": -10.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Turn the kibbutz into a co-operative community.."}, {"answerBonusVariable": "rep", "answerIdeology": "Marxist", "rep": 1.25, "reply": "You retain your communal economy. Outsiders consider you an anachronism in Israel's era of go-go capitalism. But your kibbutz contines to live as comrades. Whatever happens, you will face the future together.", "sol": 5.0, "pop": 0.0, "answerBonusValue": 10.0, "econ": 0.5, "trig": "", "answer": "Reject any form of privatization."}], "type": "B", "hook": " \"Our movement is finished. The capitalists have won.\""}, {"text": "A student group in the United States urges consumers to boycott products from your kibbutz. Their \"BDS\" protest gets media attention. The factory's managers worry the negative press will hurt your kibbutz brand. \n\n\"It's a tempest in a teapot,\" says Amos \"Let it blow over.\"\n\n\"Don't they know the kibbutz is the most progressive force in Israel?\" says Ziva \n\n\"Boycotters are Israel-hating anti-Semites!\" says Itzik \"They must be stopped!\"\n\nWhat do you do? ", "answers": [{"answerBonusVariable": "sol", "answerIdeology": "Labor Zionist", "rep": 0.5, "reply": "The BDS threats don't blow over. Your kibbutz gets associated with settlement products to be boycotted. Bad press hurts sales from your factory.", "sol": 0.0, "pop": 0.0, "answerBonusValue": 0.75, "econ": -20.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Ignore the protest."}, {"answerBonusVariable": "rep", "answerIdeology": "Socialist", "rep": 5.0, "reply": "The main BDS leaders refuse your offer but several Jewish activists visit and see you are promoting peace, not preventing it. A few  make aliyah to your kibbutz.", "sol": 5.0, "pop": 5.0, "answerBonusValue": 10.0, "econ": 0.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Invite the BDS leaders to the kibbutz to tour your factory."}, {"answerBonusVariable": "rep", "answerIdeology": "Labor Zionist", "rep": -5.0, "reply": "Your kibbutz gets caught in a social-media fight between pro-BDS and anti-BDS activists. Supporters of Israel promote your products. Your members feel united in their defense of the country.", "sol": 5.0, "pop": 0.0, "answerBonusValue": 1.25, "econ": 10.0, "trig": "", "answer": "Call the students' university to complain about their racism."}], "type": "E", "hook": "\"They should boycott the settlements, not us!\""}, {"text": "A group of young members, the grand-children and great-grandchildren of the early kibbutzniks, don't want to go to university. They don't want join the Army and choose alternative service instead.\n\n\"We plan to start small communes in poor city neighbourhoods and work as teachers and social workers,\" says Daphne, their leader. \"We will 'repair the world' by improving the lives of new immigrants and Arab-Israelis. \n\nWhat do you tell them? ", "answers": [{"answerBonusVariable": "rep", "answerIdeology": "Marxist", "rep": -5.0, "reply": "The young members stay, but they struggle to find a voice in the bureaucratic structure of your traditional kibbutz. ", "sol": -5.0, "pop": 5.0, "answerBonusValue": -10.0, "econ": 10.0, "trig": "", "answer": "They can do more good by staying on the kibbutz.  "}, {"answerBonusVariable": "rep", "answerIdeology": "Socialist", "rep": 10.0, "reply": "You hate to lose their youthful energy but you support their efforts to grow a network of urban communes. Your aging founders see in this new generation a renewal of the original ideals of the kibbutz.", "sol": 5.0, "pop": 0.75, "answerBonusValue": 10.0, "econ": 0.75, "trig": "", "answer": "Offer them funding and wish the well. "}], "type": "I", "hook": "\"Stay home and help your community!\""}]}]